WEBVTT

1
00:00:28.687 --> 00:00:30.656
(UPBEAT MUSIC PLAYING)

2
00:00:35.556 --> 00:00:38.886
<i>♪♪ Do we know where
the light is the brightest?</i>

3
00:00:38.888 --> 00:00:42.454
<i>♪♪ Do we know how to
clear what the fear is?</i>

4
00:00:42.456 --> 00:00:46.056
<i>♪♪ Do we know how to
feel when we crave it?</i>

5
00:00:46.058 --> 00:00:48.924
<i>♪♪ Do we know
what we are? ♪♪</i>

6
00:00:49.823 --> 00:00:51.054
(DOGS BARKING)

7
00:00:51.056 --> 00:00:52.324
(PANTING)

8
00:00:55.092 --> 00:00:56.159
(GRUNTS)

9
00:00:57.558 --> 00:00:58.958
(BARKING)

10
00:00:59.624 --> 00:01:01.090
(PANTING)

11
00:01:01.092 --> 00:01:03.092
(DOGS CONTINUE BARKING)

12
00:01:12.757 --> 00:01:13.758
(DOGS WHIMPERING)

13
00:01:16.159 --> 00:01:17.193
(GRUNTS)

14
00:01:22.725 --> 00:01:24.693
(HELICOPTER BLADES WHIRRING)

15
00:01:25.927 --> 00:01:27.625
(YELPS)

16
00:01:27.627 --> 00:01:29.590
EASTMAN ON MEGAPHONE:
<i>Dr. Harrison, stop.</i>

17
00:01:29.592 --> 00:01:30.858
You can't run forever.

18
00:01:30.860 --> 00:01:33.926
- (FIRING)
- (GASPS)

19
00:01:33.928 --> 00:01:37.295
<i>♪♪ Do we know where the
light is the brightest ♪♪</i>

20
00:01:38.727 --> 00:01:40.724
EASTMAN: <i>There's no escape, Doctor.</i>

21
00:01:40.726 --> 00:01:42.095
<i>You're coming with us.</i>

22
00:01:44.229 --> 00:01:45.396
(GRUNTS)

23
00:01:48.662 --> 00:01:52.263
EASTMAN: Don't use your dart
gun. We got him cornered.

24
00:01:54.895 --> 00:01:57.363
<i>♪♪ Do we know what we are ♪♪</i>

25
00:01:58.829 --> 00:02:00.930
Argh! We were so close...

26
00:02:25.832 --> 00:02:27.763
BABY ADAM: Daddy.

27
00:02:27.765 --> 00:02:30.298
- Hmm?
- Daddy. (LAUGHS)

28
00:02:30.300 --> 00:02:32.033
(SOBBING)

29
00:02:48.267 --> 00:02:50.264
- (BOY SPITS)
- (GROANS)

30
00:02:50.266 --> 00:02:51.666
(BOYS LAUGHING)

31
00:02:54.268 --> 00:02:55.899
Adam Harrison!

32
00:02:55.901 --> 00:02:57.833
Huh? Oh, yes, sir?

33
00:02:57.835 --> 00:02:59.966
No sleeping in detention.

34
00:02:59.968 --> 00:03:02.534
Use this time for something productive.

35
00:03:03.901 --> 00:03:05.168
(GROANS)

36
00:03:07.601 --> 00:03:09.900
(GROANS) What?

37
00:03:09.902 --> 00:03:12.134
- (GRUNTS)
- (BOYS LAUGHING)

38
00:03:12.136 --> 00:03:14.133
What's going on back there?

39
00:03:14.135 --> 00:03:15.632
That's disgusting!

40
00:03:15.634 --> 00:03:17.632
Adam, what's the problem?

41
00:03:17.634 --> 00:03:20.770
It looks like someone stuck
six packs of gum in my hair.

42
00:03:22.337 --> 00:03:24.267
- I didn't see nothing.
- (BOYS LAUGH)

43
00:03:24.269 --> 00:03:25.567
MR. BLAKESTONE: Tony,

44
00:03:25.569 --> 00:03:27.301
go to the office.

45
00:03:27.303 --> 00:03:28.836
Not again!

46
00:03:30.103 --> 00:03:32.105
(LAUGHS) Ow!

47
00:03:35.404 --> 00:03:37.238
You're dead, snitch!

48
00:03:40.437 --> 00:03:42.105
(KIDS CHATTERING)

49
00:03:43.405 --> 00:03:47.037
Ow. Ow! (SIGHS)

50
00:03:47.039 --> 00:03:48.639
- (GRUNTS IN FRUSTRATION)
- (RIPPING)

51
00:03:53.139 --> 00:03:56.106
Holy crap, what's happening to me? (GASPS)

52
00:03:59.939 --> 00:04:02.973
(GRUNTING) Oh!

53
00:04:06.707 --> 00:04:08.841
(KIDS LAUGHING)

54
00:04:13.141 --> 00:04:15.871
(OVERLAPPNG CHATTER AND LAUGHTER)

55
00:04:15.873 --> 00:04:18.739
Look at his shoes! (LAUGHS)

56
00:04:18.741 --> 00:04:20.575
Huh? What... What?

57
00:04:23.841 --> 00:04:25.671
(HIGH-PITCHED WHINING)

58
00:04:25.673 --> 00:04:26.805
Spaz alert.

59
00:04:26.807 --> 00:04:28.640
He used to be in my History class.

60
00:04:28.642 --> 00:04:29.973
That's why I changed classes.

61
00:04:29.975 --> 00:04:32.277
He's got like no friends.

62
00:04:33.143 --> 00:04:34.440
(GRUNTS)

63
00:04:34.442 --> 00:04:36.840
Hey, Adam. Are you okay?

64
00:04:36.842 --> 00:04:38.442
Don't run, I don't bite.

65
00:04:40.374 --> 00:04:42.241
Well, look who it is.

66
00:04:42.243 --> 00:04:44.074
How ya doing, snitch?

67
00:04:44.076 --> 00:04:45.676
Leave me alone.

68
00:04:48.542 --> 00:04:50.343
(WHISTLE BLOWS)

69
00:04:51.743 --> 00:04:53.278
(GROANING)

70
00:04:54.076 --> 00:04:55.342
(DOOR OPENS)

71
00:04:55.344 --> 00:04:58.109
Hey there, mop-top, whatcha doin'?

72
00:04:58.111 --> 00:05:00.442
Are you on your way to
the janitor's closet?

73
00:05:00.444 --> 00:05:02.309
'Cause you look like a mop!

74
00:05:02.311 --> 00:05:04.642
- (LAUGHTER)
- Good one!

75
00:05:04.644 --> 00:05:06.308
Seriously, that counts as a good one?

76
00:05:06.310 --> 00:05:07.446
Give me a break!

77
00:05:08.145 --> 00:05:09.408
- (GRUNTS)
- Good one!

78
00:05:09.410 --> 00:05:11.313
- (BOTH LAUGHING)
- That's a good one.

79
00:05:12.312 --> 00:05:13.943
(GRUNTS) Get off me!

80
00:05:13.945 --> 00:05:15.976
What? You gonna rat me out again?

81
00:05:15.978 --> 00:05:19.078
Hard to say. It depends
on the circumstances.

82
00:05:19.080 --> 00:05:20.376
Wrong answer, snitch!

83
00:05:20.378 --> 00:05:21.447
(GRUNTING)

84
00:05:23.080 --> 00:05:24.313
ADAM: Stop!

85
00:05:24.846 --> 00:05:26.478
(LAUGHS)

86
00:05:26.480 --> 00:05:27.811
Okay, you've had enough.

87
00:05:27.813 --> 00:05:29.814
Here, let me help you.

88
00:05:31.081 --> 00:05:32.579
(ALL LAUGHING)

89
00:05:32.581 --> 00:05:34.881
Look at his shoes! What a freak!

90
00:05:35.913 --> 00:05:38.281
Oh, hey, you forgot your backpack!

91
00:05:40.414 --> 00:05:42.312
Cha-ching! Two points!

92
00:05:42.314 --> 00:05:44.283
(ALL CONTINUE LAUGHING)

93
00:05:45.447 --> 00:05:46.748
Jerks...

94
00:05:49.315 --> 00:05:50.816
(SIGHS)

95
00:05:52.148 --> 00:05:54.445
SHELLY: It was those boys again wasn't it?

96
00:05:54.447 --> 00:05:56.747
No, I told you. I was playing soccer

97
00:05:56.749 --> 00:05:58.848
with my friends and the
ball hit me in the face.

98
00:05:58.850 --> 00:06:02.115
Oh, yeah? What friends
of yours play soccer?

99
00:06:02.117 --> 00:06:04.414
Uh... The British ones...

100
00:06:04.416 --> 00:06:07.149
My mates. But they call soccer "football."

101
00:06:07.151 --> 00:06:10.249
Oh, do they? And how did this happen?

102
00:06:10.251 --> 00:06:12.415
Soccer can be a dangerous sport.

103
00:06:12.417 --> 00:06:14.814
Adam, quit messing around.

104
00:06:14.816 --> 00:06:16.815
What are we going to do about this?

105
00:06:16.817 --> 00:06:18.982
Either we chop it out, or we chew it out.

106
00:06:18.984 --> 00:06:20.415
I vote chew.

107
00:06:20.417 --> 00:06:22.951
Ugh. I vote chop.

108
00:06:24.884 --> 00:06:26.284
Turn around.

109
00:06:29.250 --> 00:06:30.581
(SIGHS)

110
00:06:30.583 --> 00:06:33.452
You had such nice, long hair.

111
00:06:35.985 --> 00:06:37.885
(CONTINUES SNIPPING)

112
00:06:44.153 --> 00:06:45.385
(GARGLING)

113
00:06:45.387 --> 00:06:46.587
(SPITS)

114
00:06:49.786 --> 00:06:52.320
At least they can't make
fun of my hair anymore.

115
00:06:56.954 --> 00:06:58.188
(ALARM RINGING)

116
00:07:01.353 --> 00:07:02.687
(GASPS)

117
00:07:04.487 --> 00:07:05.787
(GROANS)

118
00:07:16.552 --> 00:07:17.122
(GASPS) Holy crap!

119
00:07:19.288 --> 00:07:21.787
Adam, You're gonna be late!

120
00:07:21.789 --> 00:07:24.153
I'll be down in a minute!

121
00:07:24.155 --> 00:07:25.656
(WHIMPERING)

122
00:07:26.890 --> 00:07:28.657
(SNIPPING)

123
00:07:30.623 --> 00:07:31.989
Adam...

124
00:07:31.991 --> 00:07:34.158
(SIGHS) That's not gonna work.

125
00:07:36.024 --> 00:07:37.854
SHELLY: What's taking so long?

126
00:07:37.856 --> 00:07:39.421
Are you all right?

127
00:07:39.423 --> 00:07:41.023
- (TOILET FLUSHING)
- ADAM: I'm fine!

128
00:07:41.025 --> 00:07:42.988
I guess your meatloaf didn't agree with me.

129
00:07:42.990 --> 00:07:45.255
I thought you loved my meatloaf.

130
00:07:45.257 --> 00:07:48.288
Love is a strong word. I like it.

131
00:07:48.290 --> 00:07:50.159
No, like's too strong.

132
00:07:51.091 --> 00:07:53.156
Hey, I hate your meatloaf.

133
00:07:53.158 --> 00:07:54.388
What?

134
00:07:54.390 --> 00:07:56.057
Listen, my meatloaf is...

135
00:07:56.059 --> 00:07:57.723
Oh, Adam.

136
00:07:57.725 --> 00:07:59.757
- What?
- That hat...

137
00:07:59.759 --> 00:08:01.423
What about it?

138
00:08:01.425 --> 00:08:03.459
That was your father's.

139
00:08:10.960 --> 00:08:12.824
Oh, sorry.

140
00:08:12.826 --> 00:08:14.158
Why are you sorry?

141
00:08:14.160 --> 00:08:15.925
I dunno.

142
00:08:15.927 --> 00:08:19.058
He died. I didn't mean to make you sad.

143
00:08:19.060 --> 00:08:20.593
(CHUCKLES SOFTLY)

144
00:08:20.595 --> 00:08:22.625
He was a great man.

145
00:08:22.627 --> 00:08:24.128
ADAM: I wish I knew him.

146
00:08:25.227 --> 00:08:27.059
(EXCLAIMING)

147
00:08:27.061 --> 00:08:30.458
I did a sloppy job on your hair.

148
00:08:30.460 --> 00:08:33.660
I must have been more tired than I thought.

149
00:08:33.662 --> 00:08:35.359
Here, let's put this back on.

150
00:08:35.361 --> 00:08:36.662
It looks good on you.

151
00:08:38.996 --> 00:08:41.593
Now hurry up, you're going
to be late for school.

152
00:08:41.595 --> 00:08:43.995
I can't believe you don't like my meatloaf.

153
00:08:43.997 --> 00:08:45.761
I'll let you in on a secret, Mom.

154
00:08:45.763 --> 00:08:46.998
Nobody likes your meatloaf.

155
00:08:50.263 --> 00:08:53.794
Okay. Well, enjoy your lunch.

156
00:08:53.796 --> 00:08:55.262
It's meatloaf, isn't it?

157
00:08:55.264 --> 00:08:57.198
- Mmm. Could be.
- (GROANS)

158
00:09:04.098 --> 00:09:07.228
EASTMAN: <i>All powerful men
have one thing in common.</i>

159
00:09:07.230 --> 00:09:10.096
- Great hair.
- (CAMERA SHUTTERS CLICKING)

160
00:09:10.098 --> 00:09:11.729
(ALL EXCLAIMING IN AWE)

161
00:09:11.731 --> 00:09:14.228
HairCo toupees have been worn in secret

162
00:09:14.230 --> 00:09:15.999
by some of the greatest men in history.

163
00:09:16.798 --> 00:09:18.965
(MEN EXCLAIMING IN AWE)

164
00:09:20.498 --> 00:09:23.430
But you're not here to
be a part of our past,

165
00:09:23.432 --> 00:09:25.965
you're here to be part of the future.

166
00:09:25.967 --> 00:09:28.767
Make no mistake, gentlemen,
hair is a growth business.

167
00:09:35.367 --> 00:09:38.801
I'm afraid we'll need to
ask you for your cameras.

168
00:09:39.399 --> 00:09:40.834
(ALL GRUMBLING)

169
00:09:47.035 --> 00:09:49.502
(CAMERA SHUTTER CLICKING)

170
00:09:51.367 --> 00:09:53.331
(STAMMERING)

171
00:09:53.333 --> 00:09:54.867
(SCANNER WHINING)

172
00:09:54.869 --> 00:09:56.366
- (BEEPING RAPIDLY)
- Huh?

173
00:09:56.368 --> 00:09:59.367
Mr. Kobayashi, I must insist.

174
00:09:59.369 --> 00:10:01.136
- Oh.
- (CHUCKLES)

175
00:10:05.502 --> 00:10:06.970
- Ooh.
- (EXCLAIMS)

176
00:10:10.269 --> 00:10:13.435
EASTMAN: This is where the magic happens.

177
00:10:13.437 --> 00:10:17.402
The future isn't toupees, no, no, no.

178
00:10:17.404 --> 00:10:19.872
The future lies in growing real hair.

179
00:10:22.137 --> 00:10:23.503
(SCREAMING)

180
00:10:23.505 --> 00:10:25.902
We're not talking about
embarrassing hair plugs,

181
00:10:25.904 --> 00:10:29.168
useless scalp massagers, or fancy shampoo.

182
00:10:29.170 --> 00:10:31.771
We're talking about genetic engineering.

183
00:10:31.773 --> 00:10:35.003
State of the art DNA manipulation.

184
00:10:35.005 --> 00:10:37.102
We're on the verge of a major breakthrough

185
00:10:37.104 --> 00:10:40.305
that will change the lives of
hundreds of millions of people...

186
00:10:41.306 --> 00:10:42.971
(MOOS)

187
00:10:42.973 --> 00:10:46.205
And make us a fortune in the process.

188
00:10:46.207 --> 00:10:48.972
(ALL SPEAKING JAPANESE)

189
00:10:48.974 --> 00:10:50.707
(HISSING)

190
00:11:01.974 --> 00:11:06.138
Dr. Billingsley is our head of
experimental research and development.

191
00:11:06.140 --> 00:11:10.439
Ah, here comes one of
our eager young interns.

192
00:11:10.441 --> 00:11:13.305
Uh, Dr. Billingsley? (CLEARS THROAT)

193
00:11:13.307 --> 00:11:15.141
I'm getting college cedit for this, right?

194
00:11:15.775 --> 00:11:17.639
Of course.

195
00:11:17.641 --> 00:11:20.376
Oh, okay. I'll just need you to
sign my work experience time sheet.

196
00:11:21.309 --> 00:11:22.941
Stand on the "X."

197
00:11:22.943 --> 00:11:24.806
Hold on, you're not
going to shoot me with...

198
00:11:24.808 --> 00:11:26.107
Ow! (GROANS)

199
00:11:26.109 --> 00:11:27.509
Ouch!

200
00:11:29.843 --> 00:11:31.474
Oh.

201
00:11:31.476 --> 00:11:32.974
Whoa.

202
00:11:32.976 --> 00:11:35.408
Oh!(LAUGHS)

203
00:11:35.410 --> 00:11:36.909
ALL: Ooh.

204
00:11:36.911 --> 00:11:39.675
Now, you may experience a
slight burning sensation.

205
00:11:39.677 --> 00:11:41.410
But don't worry about it.

206
00:11:42.477 --> 00:11:44.542
(SCREAMING)

207
00:11:44.544 --> 00:11:46.244
Help me! (SCREAMING)

208
00:11:50.378 --> 00:11:52.876
(LAUGHS NERVOUSLY) As you can see,

209
00:11:52.878 --> 00:11:55.309
we're still perfecting the formula.

210
00:11:55.311 --> 00:11:59.142
Once we do, people will
pay anything for it.

211
00:11:59.144 --> 00:12:02.843
The real money is in big hair.

212
00:12:02.845 --> 00:12:05.012
(CONTINUES SCREAMING)

213
00:12:10.581 --> 00:12:13.911
Hmm. Reduce fluoroantimonic
acid by five percent.

214
00:12:13.913 --> 00:12:17.077
- (FIRE EXTINGUISHER CLATTERS)
- (SIGHS)

215
00:12:17.079 --> 00:12:19.613
PRINCIPAL JONES: We have a no
fighting policy at this school,

216
00:12:20.747 --> 00:12:22.011
zero tolerance.

217
00:12:22.013 --> 00:12:24.745
You fight, you're suspended!

218
00:12:24.747 --> 00:12:26.845
- (MOUTHING)
- You're suspended!

219
00:12:26.847 --> 00:12:29.446
Do you hear me? Suspended!

220
00:12:29.448 --> 00:12:32.446
- (GIGGLES) You're so funny.
- (DOOR OPENS)

221
00:12:32.448 --> 00:12:34.948
Hey, you better watch your back, snitch.

222
00:12:39.981 --> 00:12:43.313
PRINCIPAL JONES: Adam Harrison.

223
00:12:43.315 --> 00:12:46.879
I believe this belongs to you.

224
00:12:46.881 --> 00:12:50.047
Nametag was on the inside.

225
00:12:50.049 --> 00:12:51.480
Oh, thank you, sir!

226
00:12:51.482 --> 00:12:55.014
Don't be throwing it into
basketball hoops anymore.

227
00:12:55.016 --> 00:12:58.281
What? Why would I throw my
own bag into a basketball hoop?

228
00:12:58.283 --> 00:13:01.517
Who knows why you kids do anything?

229
00:13:02.585 --> 00:13:06.348
Adam, you are what we call a...

230
00:13:06.350 --> 00:13:09.315
Mildred. (GRUNTS)

231
00:13:09.317 --> 00:13:14.150
Uh, what are we saying
instead of spazoid these days?

232
00:13:14.152 --> 00:13:17.282
MILDRED: Uh, normally challenged, sir.

233
00:13:17.284 --> 00:13:19.016
Oh, and, uh... (CLEARS THROAT)

234
00:13:19.018 --> 00:13:21.950
How would I say "friendless loser"?

235
00:13:21.952 --> 00:13:26.183
MILDRED: Mid-level
acquaintance deficiency.

236
00:13:26.185 --> 00:13:27.849
(GRUNTING)

237
00:13:27.851 --> 00:13:32.785
Adam, you have mid-level
acquaintance deficiency.

238
00:13:32.787 --> 00:13:34.585
Do they make a pill for that?

239
00:13:34.587 --> 00:13:36.485
- MILDRED: No, sir.
- (GULPS)

240
00:13:36.487 --> 00:13:41.318
(SIGHS) Apparently, there's
nothing we can do for you.

241
00:13:41.320 --> 00:13:44.351
This acting out needs to stop.

242
00:13:44.353 --> 00:13:45.719
But, sir...

243
00:13:45.721 --> 00:13:47.851
We have a no fighting
policy at this school.

244
00:13:47.853 --> 00:13:51.818
Zero tolerance. You
fight, you're suspended.

245
00:13:51.820 --> 00:13:53.252
Getting beat up counts as fighting?

246
00:13:53.254 --> 00:13:57.386
A fist can't punch without
a face to receive it.

247
00:13:57.388 --> 00:14:00.119
No fighting means no fighting.

248
00:14:00.121 --> 00:14:01.453
Oh, and, Adam?

249
00:14:01.455 --> 00:14:03.721
(SIGHS) Yes, sir?

250
00:14:03.723 --> 00:14:07.452
We have zero tolerance on hats.

251
00:14:07.454 --> 00:14:10.120
No hats in school.

252
00:14:10.122 --> 00:14:11.390
(SIGHS)

253
00:14:12.821 --> 00:14:14.621
And get a haircut.

254
00:14:14.623 --> 00:14:15.789
What...

255
00:14:18.022 --> 00:14:19.323
Hmm?

256
00:14:19.990 --> 00:14:21.658
(FOOTSTEPS RUNNING)

257
00:14:23.924 --> 00:14:25.191
(SIGHS)

258
00:14:32.992 --> 00:14:35.690
- (LAUGHS)
