00:28:05.391 --> 00:28:06.989
- That's you?
- Yep.

511
00:28:06.991 --> 00:28:09.323
It's you, me, and your mom.

512
00:28:09.325 --> 00:28:11.923
You were six months old.

513
00:28:11.925 --> 00:28:13.223
- Oh, man...
- (TWIG CLATTERS)

514
00:28:13.225 --> 00:28:15.090
My dad is Bigfoot?

515
00:28:15.092 --> 00:28:18.356
- Yep.
- Could my life get any worse?

516
00:28:18.358 --> 00:28:21.858
"Hey, Adam, your dad's famous,
but not like a rock star,

517
00:28:21.860 --> 00:28:25.457
"more like a hideous beast
that hides in the forest."

518
00:28:25.459 --> 00:28:27.424
Hideous? That's a bit strong.

519
00:28:27.426 --> 00:28:29.859
Are you kidding? You're a monster.

520
00:28:29.861 --> 00:28:31.190
I can see why you ran away.

521
00:28:31.192 --> 00:28:34.457
Whoa. I didn't leave because I'm a bigfoot.

522
00:28:34.459 --> 00:28:36.925
I left because I was being hunted.

523
00:28:36.927 --> 00:28:38.759
- Hunted?
- You see,

524
00:28:38.761 --> 00:28:42.793
a pharmaceutical company wanted
to turn me into a lab rat.

525
00:28:42.795 --> 00:28:45.760
I left to protect you and your mother.

526
00:28:45.762 --> 00:28:48.660
We didn't tell you for your own safety.

527
00:28:48.662 --> 00:28:50.129
What do you mean, a lab rat?

528
00:28:51.394 --> 00:28:53.360
Does your mom know you're out here?

529
00:28:53.362 --> 00:28:55.226
Yeah. She gave me the address.

530
00:28:55.228 --> 00:28:56.925
She told me to come out here...

531
00:28:56.927 --> 00:28:58.426
Alone.

532
00:28:58.428 --> 00:29:00.327
Adam, you're lying to me.

533
00:29:00.329 --> 00:29:02.693
You and mom have been
lying to me my entire life.

534
00:29:02.695 --> 00:29:04.393
We had no choice.

535
00:29:04.395 --> 00:29:06.894
You have no idea how
hard it was on both of us.

536
00:29:06.896 --> 00:29:08.528
What about me?

537
00:29:08.530 --> 00:29:11.995
It broke my heart that I couldn't
be there when you needed me.

538
00:29:11.997 --> 00:29:14.528
Adam, this is serious.

539
00:29:14.530 --> 00:29:15.861
Tell me how you found me.

540
00:29:15.863 --> 00:29:17.628
- I found your letters.
- (SIGHS)

541
00:29:17.630 --> 00:29:19.564
You took a big risk coming here.

542
00:29:20.798 --> 00:29:22.230
Your mom must be worried sick.

543
00:29:24.065 --> 00:29:25.630
Hmm? (GRUNTS)

544
00:29:25.632 --> 00:29:27.099
(TIRES SCREECH)

545
00:29:35.131 --> 00:29:37.129
- What's going on?
- Just a routine check.

546
00:29:37.131 --> 00:29:39.499
Routine? It doesn't look that way to me.

547
00:29:40.265 --> 00:29:41.564
Are you Shelly Harrison?

548
00:29:41.566 --> 00:29:44.730
What? Are you a police officer?

549
00:29:44.732 --> 00:29:47.196
I'm going to have to ask you to turn off
your engine and step out of the vehicle.

550
00:29:47.198 --> 00:29:48.767
Hmm. Okay.

551
00:29:52.399 --> 00:29:54.265
Ma'am, it's futile.

552
00:29:54.267 --> 00:29:56.266
- I suggest you get out of the car.
- (GRUNTS)

553
00:29:57.933 --> 00:30:00.098
She sent me everything. (CHUCKLES)

554
00:30:00.100 --> 00:30:02.899
I couldn't get enough of
it. She's so proud of you.

555
00:30:02.901 --> 00:30:04.864
I always thought Mom threw these out.

556
00:30:04.866 --> 00:30:06.399
Not a single one of them.

557
00:30:06.401 --> 00:30:07.932
So what about me?

558
00:30:07.934 --> 00:30:10.831
Am I gonna be... Like you?

559
00:30:10.833 --> 00:30:13.433
No. You've got nothing to worry about.

560
00:30:13.435 --> 00:30:14.932
You're already 13...

561
00:30:14.934 --> 00:30:16.832
- So what?
- Well... (SIGHS)

562
00:30:16.834 --> 00:30:18.466
You'd have symptoms by now.

563
00:30:18.468 --> 00:30:20.899
Oh, you mean like hair
that grows a foot overnight?

564
00:30:20.901 --> 00:30:22.966
Feet that blow through
the ends of my shoes?

565
00:30:22.968 --> 00:30:24.270
That kind of thing?

566
00:30:25.237 --> 00:30:27.368
I'm going to be a monster?

567
00:30:27.370 --> 00:30:29.368
It's not so bad.

568
00:30:29.370 --> 00:30:31.201
How is it not so bad?

569
00:30:31.203 --> 00:30:34.235
Spending the rest of my life
hiding in the forest like an animal?

570
00:30:34.237 --> 00:30:37.202
Slow down. What else do you have?

571
00:30:37.204 --> 00:30:41.135
The hair thing, the feet.
What about your ears?

572
00:30:41.137 --> 00:30:44.902
When your adrenaline's up,
does your hearing change?

573
00:30:44.904 --> 00:30:46.901
Sometimes it gets super loud.

574
00:30:46.903 --> 00:30:48.637
Like a migraine or something.

575
00:30:48.639 --> 00:30:50.570
When's the last time you shaved your hands?

576
00:30:50.572 --> 00:30:51.903
What? Ew! Never!

577
00:30:51.905 --> 00:30:53.068
But you shave your back?

578
00:30:53.070 --> 00:30:54.902
No. I don't shave anything.

579
00:30:54.904 --> 00:30:58.704
This is amazing. My hands
and back are where it started.

580
00:30:58.706 --> 00:31:03.104
By the time I was 12, I was waxing
my back every weekend with duct tape.

581
00:31:03.106 --> 00:31:04.903
But you're different.

582
00:31:04.905 --> 00:31:07.004
It's like you've got all the
good stuff, but none of the fur.

583
00:31:07.006 --> 00:31:09.338
How is any of this "good stuff"?

584
00:31:09.340 --> 00:31:12.606
There's a lot of good
things about being a bigfoot.

585
00:31:12.608 --> 00:31:15.208
You're standing on that leg, aren't you?

586
00:31:19.039 --> 00:31:20.373
(ADAM SCREAMING)

587
00:31:23.608 --> 00:31:26.105
(HEAVY FOOTSTEPS RUNNING)

588
00:31:26.107 --> 00:31:27.475
(ADAM GRUNTING)

589
00:31:28.142 --> 00:31:29.275
(ADAM GROANS)

590
00:31:36.108 --> 00:31:38.574
You... You fixed my leg.

591
00:31:38.576 --> 00:31:40.140
How is that possible?

592
00:31:40.142 --> 00:31:43.541
The healing touch, fast
growing hair, big feet...

593
00:31:43.543 --> 00:31:45.406
It all goes with the territory.

594
00:31:45.408 --> 00:31:47.540
Holy moly. What are you?

595
00:31:47.542 --> 00:31:49.374
Some kind of hairy wizard?

596
00:31:49.376 --> 00:31:52.207
Ha. Nothing that exciting.

597
00:31:52.209 --> 00:31:54.710
We've got to find out what else you can do.

598
00:31:55.510 --> 00:31:56.809
Hang on to this.

599
00:31:58.077 --> 00:31:59.243
What's it do?

600
00:32:00.577 --> 00:32:01.612
(ADAM SCREAMING)

601
00:32:06.043 --> 00:32:07.944
- (CONTINUES SCREAMING)
- (BIGFOOT YELLS)

602
00:32:08.910 --> 00:32:10.312
BIGFOOT: Whoo-hoo!

603
00:32:12.879 --> 00:32:14.677
(ADAM CONTINUES SCREAMING)

604
00:32:14.679 --> 00:32:15.943
BIGFOOT: Whoo-hoo!

605
00:32:15.945 --> 00:32:17.146
(GROWLS)

606
00:32:25.112 --> 00:32:26.179
ADAM: Whoa!

607
00:32:28.213 --> 00:32:30.247
(GASPING)

608
00:32:31.646 --> 00:32:32.812
(ADAM GRUNTING)

609
00:32:35.447 --> 00:32:38.981
BIGFOOT: (LAUGHS) Whoa! (GRUNTS)

610
00:32:39.914 --> 00:32:41.980
(GASPING)

611
00:32:45.480 --> 00:32:46.913
What's going on? It hurts!

612
00:32:47.446 --> 00:32:48.614
(BUZZING LOUDLY)

613
00:32:48.616 --> 00:32:50.779
- (THUDDING)
- (BEES BUZZING LOUDLY)

614
00:32:50.781 --> 00:32:52.380
(BIRDS SQUAWKING LOUDLY)

615
00:32:52.382 --> 00:32:53.745
- (HIGH-PITCHED RINGING)
- (GROANS)

616
00:32:53.747 --> 00:32:55.613
Just relax...

617
00:32:55.615 --> 00:32:58.413
That was so irresponsible!
You could've killed me!

618
00:32:58.415 --> 00:33:00.413
It's the adrenaline.

619
00:33:00.415 --> 00:33:02.448
- Calm down.
- (BREATHING RAPIDLY)

620
00:33:02.450 --> 00:33:04.912
- Take a deep breath.
- (BREATHES DEEPLY)

621
00:33:04.914 --> 00:33:07.616
That's it. And listen.

622
00:33:10.183 --> 00:33:12.251
(TAPPING)

623
00:33:14.017 --> 00:33:16.415
- Whoa. It's a woodpecker.
- (LAUGHS)

624
00:33:16.417 --> 00:33:17.783
Focus over there.

625
00:33:27.319 --> 00:33:29.383
That's a... What do you call it?

626
00:33:29.385 --> 00:33:31.883
- A geyser.
- It's like I can see it.

627
00:33:31.885 --> 00:33:33.882
The sound makes a picture in your head.

628
00:33:33.884 --> 00:33:37.651
Dolphins and bats have something
similar called echolocation.

629
00:33:38.352 --> 00:33:39.916
Pretty cool, Huh?

630
00:33:39.918 --> 00:33:43.116
I guess. Well, Batman's cool...

631
00:33:43.118 --> 00:33:44.549
Dolphinman, not so much.

632
00:33:44.551 --> 00:33:46.649
And your feet... Tell me you've tried them?

633
00:33:46.651 --> 00:33:47.918
Ditch the shoes, buddy.

634
00:33:51.453 --> 00:33:52.951
- Ah!
- What?

635
00:33:52.953 --> 00:33:54.117
It's cold.

636
00:33:54.119 --> 00:33:57.084
- (LAUGHS) Try to keep up.
- Huh?

637
00:33:57.086 --> 00:33:59.051
- Whoo-hoo!
- Wait!

638
00:33:59.053 --> 00:34:00.788
(GRUNTING)

639
00:34:03.221 --> 00:34:05.085
MAN: <i>♪♪ Where you belong</i>

640
00:34:05.087 --> 00:34:06.452
(GRUNTING)

641
00:34:06.454 --> 00:34:09.154
<i>♪♪ Dark days are gone</i>

642
00:34:10.187 --> 00:34:12.953
<i>♪♪ Somebody new</i>

643
00:34:12.955 --> 00:34:15.085
<i>♪♪ Takes us along ♪♪</i>

644
00:34:15.087 --> 00:34:16.353
ADAM: Whoo-hoo!

645
00:34:16.355 --> 00:34:18.354
This is amazing!

646
00:34:18.356 --> 00:34:19.919
Feels good, doesn't it?

647
00:34:19.921 --> 00:34:22.289
Yeah! It's the greatest feeling in the...

648
00:34:22.954 --> 00:34:25.053
(GRUNTING)

649
00:34:25.055 --> 00:34:26.420
(LAUGHS)

650
00:34:26.422 --> 00:34:27.989
BIGFOOT: Whoo-hoo!

651
00:34:28.821 --> 00:34:30.622
(BOTH LAUGHING)

652
00:34:34.621 --> 00:34:36.120
ADAM: Whoo!

653
00:34:36.122 --> 00:34:37.923
(LAUGHING)

654
00:34:39.756 --> 00:34:40.924
Whoo!

655
00:34:46.057 --> 00:34:47.757
Whoo-hoo! Oh!

656
00:34:48.290 --> 00:34:49.956
Whoo... (GRUNTS)

657
00:34:49.958 --> 00:34:51.491
Ouch, buddy. Oh.

658
00:34:51.493 --> 00:34:53.957
- I'm so sorry. I should've warned you.
- (GROANS)

659
00:34:53.959 --> 00:34:57.556
You've gotta avoid smashing
head first into the trees.

660
00:34:57.558 --> 00:34:59.623
(GROANING)

661
00:34:59.625 --> 00:35:02.124
I think I'm done with
bigfoot lessons for the day.

662
00:35:02.126 --> 00:35:03.589
There's one more thing.

663
00:35:03.591 --> 00:35:05.591
Does it involve smashing
head first into anything?

664
00:35:05.593 --> 00:35:08.290
Nope. I can talk to animals.

665
00:35:08.292 --> 00:35:09.456
Are you kidding?

666
00:35:09.458 --> 00:35:10.890
Just watch. (WHISTLES)

667
00:35:10.892 --> 00:35:12.590
Hey, Steve, come over here.

668
00:35:12.592 --> 00:35:14.160
(BIRD CHIRPING)

669
00:35:21.727 --> 00:35:23.757
(LAUGHING)

670
00:35:23.759 --> 00:35:25.892
- So what did you say to her?
- (CHIRPING)

671
00:35:25.894 --> 00:35:28.726
(LAUGHING) I love it.

672
00:35:28.728 --> 00:35:31.392
I just hear chirps. I
guess I don't have that one.

673
00:35:31.394 --> 00:35:35.862
Give it a shot. The secret
here is to slow things down.

674
00:35:37.961 --> 00:35:39.795
(CHIRPING)

675
00:35:41.128 --> 00:35:43.592
(CHIRPING)

676
00:35:43.594 --> 00:35:45.060
(DISTORTED) Nice to finally meet you, Adam.

677
00:35:45.062 --> 00:35:47.160
You look better in real
life than in your photo.

678
00:35:47.162 --> 00:35:48.961
- No way.
- Yes way.

679
00:35:48.963 --> 00:35:50.261
It works!

680
00:35:50.263 --> 00:35:53.162
It... Is... Nice... To... Meet... You!

681
00:35:53.164 --> 00:35:55.260
- (STEVE LAUGHS)
- You don't need to talk like that.

682
00:35:55.262 --> 00:35:56.727
They understand you just fine.

683
00:35:56.729 --> 00:35:59.127
VOICE FROM TREE: What am I? Chopped liver?

684
00:35:59.129 --> 00:36:02.395
Sheesh. He doesn't even introduce me!

685
00:36:02.397 --> 00:36:04.228
The trees talk too?

686
00:36:04.230 --> 00:36:05.630
This place is like a Disney movie!

687
00:36:06.731 --> 00:36:09.229
Hello... Oh!

688
00:36:09.231 --> 00:36:12.296
Trees don't talk, you stupid idiot.

689
00:36:12.298 --> 00:36:13.895
(LAUGHS) That's just Trapper.

690
00:36:13.897 --> 00:36:15.628
(GRUNTING)

691
00:36:15.630 --> 00:36:17.728
<i>Enchante.</i> Ow!

692
00:36:17.730 --> 00:36:20.529
Oh, yeah. This is my lovely wife, Weecha.

693
00:36:20.531 --> 00:36:22.130
She's also <i>enchanted.</i>

694
00:36:22.132 --> 00:36:23.729
Oh. Hello.

695
00:36:23.731 --> 00:36:25.365
Nice to finally meet you, Adam.

696
00:36:25.367 --> 00:36:27.797
Your dad talks about you all the time.

697
00:36:27.799 --> 00:36:29.397
Every real man has a son.

698
00:36:29.399 --> 00:36:31.297
I got kids on the way myself.

699
00:36:31.299 --> 00:36:32.730
All boys.

700
00:36:32.732 --> 00:36:34.430
WEECHA: (LAUGHING) We don't know that.

701
00:36:34.432 --> 00:36:36.263
I can tell.

702
00:36:36.265 --> 00:36:39.334
How you doin', fellas? Gettin'
big and strong in there? Good.

703
00:36:40.667 --> 00:36:42.097
I have to say...

704
00:36:42.099 --> 00:36:44.598
- The kid doesn't look like a bigfoot.
- Trapper!

705
00:36:44.600 --> 00:36:46.632
What? I'm just calling it like it is.

706
00:36:46.634 --> 00:36:49.833
You've all got eyes. This is a bigfoot.

707
00:36:49.835 --> 00:36:52.665
This is a boy. It's Humans 101.

708
00:36:52.667 --> 00:36:55.932
Don't listen to Trapper. Nobody here does.

709
00:36:55.934 --> 00:36:59.099
Are you kidding? (LAUGHS)
I'm like the boss around here!

710
00:36:59.101 --> 00:37:02.400
Everybody in this forest
hangs off my every word.

711
00:37:02.402 --> 00:37:05.201
(LAUGHS) Is he always like that?

712
00:37:05.203 --> 00:37:06.636
What a place.

713
00:37:07.869 --> 00:37:09.669
(GRUNTS) I'm starting to like it here.

714
00:37:12.969 --> 00:37:14.801
- (GROWLS)
- (YELPS)

715
00:37:14.803 --> 00:37:16.770
Don't run and don't turn your back to him.

716
00:37:18.469 --> 00:37:20.604
- Oh, no. He's a big one!
- (WHIMPERING)

717
00:37:21.270 --> 00:37:22.570
(GROWLING)

718
00:37:23.803 --> 00:37:25.438
- Careful, Dad! Don't...
- (YELLING)

719
00:37:29.470 --> 00:37:31.738
(BOTH LAUGHING)

720
00:37:32.938 --> 00:37:36.635
Nice performance, Wilbur. 10 out of 10!

721
00:37:36.637 --> 00:37:40.104
Well, thanks. I've been practicing.

722
00:37:40.106 --> 00:37:42.737
You jerk! I almost had a heart attack.

723
00:37:42.739 --> 00:37:44.236
(LAUGHING) Nothing to be afraid of.

724
00:37:44.238 --> 00:37:45.937
This is just Wilbur.

725
00:37:45.939 --> 00:37:49.170
He's a big teddy bear,
sweeter than a pot of honey.

726
00:37:49.172 --> 00:37:50.839
I am not!

727
00:37:51.671 --> 00:37:54.305
Okay, maybe I am.

728
00:37:54.307 --> 00:37:55.837
This is my son, Adam.

729
00:37:55.839 --> 00:37:58.170
Pleased to meet you, kid.

730
00:37:58.172 --> 00:38:00.272
Over the hill... (PANTING)

731
00:38:00.274 --> 00:38:02.739
Oh, hello. (PANTING)

732
00:38:02.741 --> 00:38:05.072
- Two of 'em... (PANTING)
- Wow, slow down, Tina.

733
00:38:05.074 --> 00:38:06.938
- Breathe through your nose.
- (BREATHING RAPIDLY)

734
00:38:06.940 --> 00:38:09.240
I ain't got time to
breathe through my nose!

735
00:38:09.242 --> 00:38:11.771
I'm talkin' about rednecks with guns!

736
00:38:11.773 --> 00:38:14.639
Hoo-hoo, hunters! (LAUGHS)

737
00:38:14.641 --> 00:38:16.405
Hunters? Should we hide?

738
00:38:16.407 --> 00:38:19.142
(CHUCKLES) That won't be necessary.

739
00:38:21.041 --> 00:38:23.706
I, my friend, am a connoisseur

740
00:38:23.708 --> 00:38:25.607
and when it comes to hamburgers,

741
00:38:25.609 --> 00:38:29.373
this is a tasty piece of beef.

742
00:38:29.375 --> 00:38:31.706
I thought you got the fried chicken.

743
00:38:31.708 --> 00:38:36.141
My point is, whatever
it is, it's delicious.

744
00:38:36.143 --> 00:38:37.908
(ALL PANTING)

745
00:38:37.910 --> 00:38:40.610
We haven't had hunters in three seasons!

746
00:38:42.443 --> 00:38:45.340
BIGFOOT: Blue 32. Green 180. Hut!

747
00:38:45.342 --> 00:38:46.774
- (GRUNTS)
- (TINA SQUEALS)

748
00:38:46.776 --> 00:38:48.574
Yee-haw!

749
00:38:48.576 --> 00:38:51.775
You think that'd be cruelty
to animals, but she loves it.

750
00:38:51.777 --> 00:38:53.178
(TINA CONTINUES YELLING)

751
00:38:55.511 --> 00:38:57.342
TOM: My point is,

752
00:38:57.344 --> 00:38:59.309
we're smarter than them animals,

753
00:38:59.311 --> 00:39:02.312
so they deserve to die.

754
00:39:16.879 --> 00:39:18.377
(TAPPING)

755
00:39:18.379 --> 00:39:20.444
That's the sign. (LAUGHS)

756
00:39:20.446 --> 00:39:22.144
(SHUSHING)

757
00:39:22.146 --> 00:39:24.044
(GROWLING SOFTLY)

758
00:39:24.046 --> 00:39:25.013
(KNUCKLES CRACKING)

759
00:39:28.915 --> 00:39:31.979
It's a dog-eat-dog
world, my friend,

760
00:39:31.981 --> 00:39:33.711
but I ain't eatin' no dog.

761
00:39:33.713 --> 00:39:35.879
Which brings me back to my hamburger.

762
00:39:35.881 --> 00:39:37.746
TOM: That would be a chicken burger.

763
00:39:37.748 --> 00:39:39.116
TIM: Whatever burger.

764
00:39:41.949 --> 00:39:43.016
(GROANS)

765
00:39:45.849 --> 00:39:47.747
(BURPS)

766
00:39:47.749 --> 00:39:49.479
(BURPING)

767
00:39:49.481 --> 00:39:50.950
(BOTH LAUGHING)

768
00:39:54.616 --> 00:39:56.313
(GROWLING)

769
00:39:56.315 --> 00:39:57.316
Oh!

770
00:39:57.983 --> 00:39:59.350
I got it!

771
00:40:00.082 --> 00:40:01.349
I saw it first!

772
00:40:02.984 --> 00:40:04.484
(GROANING)

773
00:40:07.684 --> 00:40:10.282
(LAUGHING) We got him, my friend!

774
00:40:10.284 --> 00:40:14.150
(LAUGHING) I told you dousing
ourselves in that bear urine

775
00:40:14.152 --> 00:40:15.816
would make us in-detectable.

776
00:40:15.818 --> 00:40:17.249
Like the Invisible Man.

777
00:40:17.251 --> 00:40:19.917
Ooh, you were right about that one, buddy.

778
00:40:19.919 --> 00:40:23.315
All we gotta do before we mount it
on the wall is make sure it's dead.

779
00:40:23.317 --> 00:40:24.685
Let's take a look.

780
00:40:26.919 --> 00:40:28.884
Yup. He's a goner.

781
00:40:28.886 --> 00:40:33.817
(LAUGHING) I love destroying
nature's most majestic creatures!

782
00:40:33.819 --> 00:40:37.084
Come on, get your butt
in here. Selfie time!

783
00:40:37.086 --> 00:40:38.287
(CAMERA SHUTTER CLICKING)

784
00:40:42.120 --> 00:40:44.818
(LAUGHING) <i>I'm gonna
post that up on Facebook,</i>

785
00:40:44.820 --> 00:40:46.584
<i>and watch the likes come rollin' in.</i>

786
00:40:46.586 --> 00:40:48.618
<i>Oh, don't you be tagging me!</i>

787
00:40:48.620 --> 00:40:51.319
<i>My wife thinks I'm down at the
community college studyin' to be an...</i>

788
00:40:51.321 --> 00:40:52.485
(ROARING)

789
00:40:52.487 --> 00:40:53.988
(BOTH SCREAM)

790
00:40:55.321 --> 00:40:58.121
- (GROWLING)
- Zombie bear!

791
00:40:58.988 --> 00:41:00.622
He's undead!

792
00:41:02.521 --> 00:41:04.055
I did poke it!

793
00:41:08.255 --> 00:41:09.522
(SCREAMS)

794
00:41:11.355 --> 00:41:13.888
(GRUNTS) And stay out!

795
00:41:13.890 --> 00:41:16.220
- (LAUGHING)
- Nice shot, honey.

796
00:41:16.222 --> 00:41:20.121
(LAUGHS) They won't be
coming back for a while.

797
00:41:20.123 --> 00:41:23.322
(LAUGHS) That was the
best thing I've ever seen!

798
00:41:23.724 --> 00:41:24.924
(GROANS)

799
00:41:26.624 --> 00:41:28.488
At least you guys know
how to have a good time.

800
00:41:28.490 --> 00:41:31.221
We make the most of it.

801
00:41:31.223 --> 00:41:33.222
ADAM: It's nice to finally have a dad.

802
00:41:33.224 --> 00:41:36.154
Well, then, son, we've got
to make up for lost time.

803
00:41:36.156 --> 00:41:38.155
All right. Where do we start?

804
00:41:38.157 --> 00:41:39.924
I don't know.

805
00:41:39.926 --> 00:41:45.490
Okay, so what's the best
father-son thing you can think of?

806
00:41:45.492 --> 00:41:48.455
Hmm... Uh... Want to play baseball?

807
00:41:48.457 --> 00:41:51.159
- Sure, why not? You got a ball?
- Hmm.

808
00:41:54.027 --> 00:41:56.290
Whoa, I would have picked
a different activity

809
00:41:56.292 --> 00:41:58.757
if I'd known you had to
whittle a ball from scratch.

810
00:41:58.759 --> 00:42:00.324
That's how things work around here.

811
00:42:00.326 --> 00:42:02.025
You have to rely on yourself.

812
00:42:02.027 --> 00:42:04.457
Yeah. I guess you can't just
order it off the Internet.

813
00:42:04.459 --> 00:42:06.692
What's the Internet?

814
00:42:06.694 --> 00:42:09.358
You've never heard of the
Internet? Are you kidding me?

815
00:42:09.360 --> 00:42:10.958
(LAUGHS) Adam, I'm joking.

816
00:42:10.960 --> 00:42:13.591
I know what the Internet is. Come on!

817
00:42:13.593 --> 00:42:16.327
I have tons of friends on MySpace.

818
00:42:17.561 --> 00:42:20.391
Things have changed a little bit.

819
00:42:20.393 --> 00:42:21.758
You'll see when you come back.

820
00:42:21.760 --> 00:42:24.127
Oh, Adam, I told you. I can't.

821
00:42:25.461 --> 00:42:28.493
(SIGHS) I'm sorry, I know how you feel.

822
00:42:28.495 --> 00:42:30.129
Come on, son, show me what you got.

823
00:42:31.062 --> 00:42:32.460
Okay, Pops.

824
00:42:32.462 --> 00:42:34.393
(BOTH GRUNTING)

825
00:42:34.395 --> 00:42:35.595
Huh?

826
00:42:37.063 --> 00:42:38.964
(BOTH GRUNTING)

827
00:42:40.063 --> 00:42:42.226
(TOM SCREAMING)

828
00:42:42.228 --> 00:42:45.160
Whoa, maybe we should try something else.

829
00:42:45.162 --> 00:42:46.327
Hmm.

830
00:42:46.329 --> 00:42:48.063
BIGFOOT: Whoo-hoo!

831
00:42:48.764 --> 00:42:50.063
ADAM: Whoo!

832
00:42:52.763 --> 00:42:54.697
(BOTH LAUGHING)

833
00:42:57.164 --> 00:42:59.294
(INDISTINCT CHATTERING)

834
00:42:59.296 --> 00:43:01.328
(BOTH LAUGHING)

835
00:43:01.330 --> 00:43:03.029
(SIGHS)

836
00:43:03.031 --> 00:43:04.832
Whoa, that felt great.

837
00:43:07.265 --> 00:43:08.829
(LAUGHS)

838
00:43:08.831 --> 00:43:10.996
(BOTH LAUGHING)

839
00:43:10.998 --> 00:43:13.264
Ah, come on out, I'll race you back.

840
00:43:13.266 --> 00:43:16.197
All right, old man, bring it on.

841
00:43:16.199 --> 00:43:18.467
(MUSIC PLAYING)

842
00:43:24.800 --> 00:43:26.732
(PANTING) Give me a second.

843
00:43:26.734 --> 00:43:29.064
What's wrong, gettin' tired?

844
00:43:29.066 --> 00:43:30.632
You wish.

845
00:43:30.634 --> 00:43:32.298
Whoo-hoo!

846
00:43:32.300 --> 00:43:34.168
Hey, no fair!

847
00:43:41.567 --> 00:43:43.498
(PANTING)

848
00:43:43.500 --> 00:43:45.134
(TUNING GUITAR)

849
00:43:47.435 --> 00:43:49.800
(LAUGHS) You totally cheated!

850
00:43:49.802 --> 00:43:51.970
(LAUGHS) We'll call it a tie.

851
00:43:52.802 --> 00:43:55.167
Whoa! Did you make this?

852
00:43:55.169 --> 00:43:57.634
Sure did. So do you play?

853
00:43:57.636 --> 00:43:59.369
Oh, yeah. I love guitar!

854
00:44:02.869 --> 00:44:04.804
(PLAYING OFF-KEY)

855
00:44:05.437 --> 00:44:07.034
Yeah, uh,

856
00:44:07.036 --> 00:44:09.168
try not squeezing so tight.

857
00:44:09.170 --> 00:44:12.971
Yeah, leave a little
space... Yeah, yeah. Oh. Okay.

858
00:44:15.672 --> 00:44:17.802
I think it's out of tune or something.

859
00:44:17.804 --> 00:44:20.636
Do you play or is it just to look cool?

860
00:44:20.638 --> 00:44:22.872
Well, you'll be the judge.

861
00:44:23.470 --> 00:44:25.704
(PLAYING GUITAR)

862
00:44:45.639 --> 00:44:47.171
Holy crap!

863
00:44:47.173 --> 00:44:49.504
Well, I've had lots of time to practice.

864
00:44:49.506 --> 00:44:51.505
Can you teach me how to do that?

865
00:44:51.507 --> 00:44:54.471
Well, maybe a little
bit more rock and roll.

866
00:44:54.473 --> 00:44:56.374
Of course, I'd be happy to.

867
00:44:57.006 --> 00:44:59.307
(STRUMMING)

868
00:45:02.007 --> 00:45:03.539
You have to come home with me.

869
00:45:03.541 --> 00:45:07.506
Oh, Adam, I wish I
could, but it's not safe.

870
00:45:07.508 --> 00:45:10.972
We can keep you a secret.
No one will ever know.

871
00:45:10.974 --> 00:45:12.806
They don't even know you're alive!

872
00:45:12.808 --> 00:45:14.505
HairCo will find out.

873
00:45:14.507 --> 00:45:17.106
I'm sure they've been
monitoring you and your mom.

874
00:45:17.108 --> 00:45:21.040
They're relentless. I've seen it firsthand.

875
00:45:21.042 --> 00:45:22.939
When I was in medical school,

876
00:45:22.941 --> 00:45:24.906
<i>I started studying my hair growth,</i>

877
00:45:24.908 --> 00:45:28.775
<i>desperately trying to make sense
of what was happening to me.</i>

878
00:45:28.777 --> 00:45:32.074
<i>I discovered a rare DNA
mutation in my blood</i>

879
00:45:32.076 --> 00:45:35.509
<i>was triggering a resurgence
of Neanderthal features.</i>

880
00:45:35.511 --> 00:45:37.944
<i>Every day I was becoming
more of a bigfoot.</i>

881
00:45:39.177 --> 00:45:41.909
<i>HairCo found out
about my experiments.</i>

882
00:45:41.911 --> 00:45:44.908
<i>At first they tried to hire me</i>

883
00:45:44.910 --> 00:45:47.976
<i>but when I declined,
my lab was ransacked,</i>

884
00:45:47.978 --> 00:45:50.844
<i>and all my research stolen.</i>

885
00:45:50.846 --> 00:45:53.176
<i>That's when things got
really out of control.</i>

886
00:45:53.178 --> 00:45:55.009
<i>They threatened your mother.</i>

887
00:45:55.011 --> 00:45:57.876
<i>We couldn't go anywhere
without being followed.</i>

888
00:45:57.878 --> 00:46:02.010
I knew the only way to keep
you safe was to disappear.

889
00:46:02.012 --> 00:46:05.544
Why didn't they come after me?
Don't we have the same, uh...

890
00:46:05.546 --> 00:46:08.811
DNA. Yes, we do, but when you were younger,

891
00:46:08.813 --> 00:46:11.710
the genetic mutation hadn't activated yet.

892
00:46:11.712 --> 00:46:16.012
I'm sure they found some of your genetic
material when they ransacked the house.

893
00:46:16.014 --> 00:46:18.877
But back then, you'd have
seemed totally normal.

894
00:46:18.879 --> 00:46:20.479
That must be why they left us alone.

895
00:46:20.481 --> 00:46:23.145
And it's the reason I can't come back.

896
00:46:23.147 --> 00:46:25.979
It's too dangerous. If
they even suspect I'm alive,

897
00:46:25.981 --> 00:46:28.148
they'll stop at nothing
to get what they want.

898
00:46:30.915 --> 00:46:31.881
(GRUNTS)

899
00:46:32.615 --> 00:46:33.781
You.

900
00:46:33.783 --> 00:46:35.079
What are you doing here?

901
00:46:35.081 --> 00:46:37.313
All day breakfast, of course.

902
00:46:37.315 --> 00:46:41.080
I jest. Please sit, Mrs. Harrison,

903
00:46:41.082 --> 00:46:44.848
so that we might solve the
problem of your missing boy.

904
00:46:44.850 --> 00:46:47.148
(SIGHS) He hates that photo.

905
00:46:47.150 --> 00:46:49.481
You expect me to believe
you're here because of my son?

906
00:46:49.483 --> 00:46:50.949
Oh, you got me.

907
00:46:50.951 --> 00:46:52.915
I don't care about your son,

908
00:46:52.917 --> 00:46:56.218
but if we find him, we find your husband.

909
00:46:56.982 --> 00:46:58.649
My husband?

910
00:46:58.651 --> 00:47:00.716
He died a long time ago. You know that.

911
00:47:00.718 --> 00:47:02.616
Yes, well... No.

912
00:47:02.618 --> 00:47:06.352
Some new evidence has come to my
attention. Please read the headline.

913
00:47:07.719 --> 00:47:09.318
"Baby born in a pumpkin."

914
00:47:10.618 --> 00:47:12.718
The other headline.

915
00:47:14.652 --> 00:47:17.050
Bigfoot? Really?

916
00:47:17.052 --> 00:47:22.116
Before he disappeared, your husband
was working on strange experiments.

917
00:47:22.118 --> 00:47:26.485
Studying hair growth.
Hair like we've never seen.

918
00:47:26.487 --> 00:47:29.354
Hair like that of say, a bigfoot.

919
00:47:30.954 --> 00:47:33.851
Quite a coincidence, wouldn't you say?

920
00:47:33.853 --> 00:47:39.619
Your son happens to show up at the
first Bigfoot sighting in 10 years?

921
00:47:39.621 --> 00:47:42.620
I don't think your husband
was studying Bigfoot.

922
00:47:42.622 --> 00:47:45.088
I think he is Bigfoot.

923
00:47:45.521 --> 00:47:47.687
(GRUNTING)

924
00:47:47.689 --> 00:47:51.118
Ta-da! And you said I don't
wine and dine you anymore.

925
00:47:51.120 --> 00:47:53.086
Something isn't right.

926
00:47:53.088 --> 00:47:54.988
I thought you might say that.

927
00:47:55.788 --> 00:47:57.655
Perfect-issimo.

928
00:47:57.657 --> 00:48:01.053
A beautiful meal for my beautiful wife,

929
00:48:01.055 --> 00:48:03.387
and my
soon-to-be-born sons.

930
00:48:03.389 --> 00:48:06.522
Eat up boys, no runts in this litter!

931
00:48:06.524 --> 00:48:11.757
Shh, I'm serious. What are all
these black cars doing here?

932
00:48:13.956 --> 00:48:15.257
Oh, no.

933
00:48:16.457 --> 00:48:19.022
I know. He hates that photo.

934
00:48:19.024 --> 00:48:20.158
(GRUNTING)

935
00:48:23.958 --> 00:48:27.022
(WHISPERING) That's Bigfoot's wife.

936
00:48:27.024 --> 00:48:29.155
We're not leaving until we find him.

937
00:48:29.157 --> 00:48:32.292
Tear the forest down if you have to.

938
00:48:34.425 --> 00:48:36.924
Yuck. Looks way too healthy.

939
00:48:36.926 --> 00:48:39.157
Well, it is. And tastes good too.

940
00:48:39.159 --> 00:48:40.923
Ooh, don't you have any meat?

941
00:48:40.925 --> 00:48:42.525
I'm afraid not.

942
00:48:42.527 --> 00:48:45.158
You kind of have to be
a vegetarian out here.

943
00:48:45.160 --> 00:48:48.524
You eat one of those guys and
everyone starts asking questions.

944
00:48:48.526 --> 00:48:50.425
Oh, no, who ate Trapper?

945
00:48:50.427 --> 00:48:53.858
- Where's Trapper? Have you seen Trapper?
- (LAUGHS)

946
00:48:53.860 --> 00:48:55.658
You can try to reason with them,

947
00:48:55.660 --> 00:48:58.157
but nobody cares that he's delicious.

948
00:48:58.159 --> 00:48:59.391
I am trying to tell them, you know,

949
00:48:59.393 --> 00:49:01.825
a little salt and pepper
on the old Trapper,

950
00:49:01.827 --> 00:49:04.460
it's so good. They don't want to hear it.

951
00:49:04.462 --> 00:49:06.895
Oh, I see how that could be awkward.

952
00:49:07.462 --> 00:49:08.859
Whoa, hot.

953
00:49:08.861 --> 00:49:10.726
Hot but good, right?

954
00:49:10.728 --> 00:49:12.459
No... Just hot.

955
00:49:12.461 --> 00:49:13.859
You have to admit,

956
00:49:13.861 --> 00:49:15.327
it's better than Mom's meatloaf.

957
00:49:15.329 --> 00:49:18.394
I'll give you that. What
is in that stuff anyway?

958
00:49:18.396 --> 00:49:22.160
Car tires, wet cardboard
boxes and lots of ketchup.

959
00:49:22.162 --> 00:49:24.127
(BOTH LAUGHING)

960
00:49:24.129 --> 00:49:26.627
(PANTING)

961
00:49:26.629 --> 00:49:28.461
We got a big problem.

962
00:49:28.463 --> 00:49:30.095
What's this?

963
00:49:30.097 --> 00:49:31.660
We saw Adam's mom. They
got her locked in a trailer.

964
00:49:31.662 --> 00:49:32.862
- Shelly?
- Mom?

965
00:49:32.864 --> 00:49:34.661
Hold on, it gets worse.

966
00:49:34.663 --> 00:49:37.230
There are a bazillion dudes
in suits heading this way.

967
00:49:47.264 --> 00:49:48.231
(SIZZLING)

968
00:49:48.931 --> 00:49:50.629
I'm sorry... I...

969
00:49:50.631 --> 00:49:52.463
You led them right to us.

970
00:49:52.465 --> 00:49:56.162
And what's worse, you
put your mother in danger!

971
00:49:56.164 --> 00:49:58.131
- I...
- Adam, what have you done?

972
00:49:58.133 --> 00:49:59.430
I didn't mean to.

973
00:49:59.432 --> 00:50:02.297
Actions have consequences.

974
00:50:02.299 --> 00:50:05.197
You should never have come here.

975
00:50:05.199 --> 00:50:07.465
Well, you better do something.

976
00:50:07.467 --> 00:50:10.796
If they find Bigfoot, the jig is up!

977
00:50:10.798 --> 00:50:11.897
I can fix this!

978
00:50:11.899 --> 00:50:13.164
What are you doing?

979
00:50:13.166 --> 00:50:14.798
I'll tell them I'm okay. It'll be fine.

980
00:50:14.800 --> 00:50:16.965
No, Adam, you don't know
who you're dealing with...

981
00:50:16.967 --> 00:50:17.934
(SIGHS)

982
00:50:24.899 --> 00:50:26.034
Please be safe.

983
00:50:27.868 --> 00:50:29.665
Over here, you found me!

984
00:50:29.667 --> 00:50:32.199
Adam Harrison, the missing boy.

985
00:50:32.201 --> 00:50:34.802
Everything's fine. We can all go home. Oh!

986
00:50:36.168 --> 00:50:37.169
(EXHALES)

987
00:50:44.936 --> 00:50:46.633
Mom!

988
00:50:46.635 --> 00:50:48.434
Oh, thank you, thank you, thank you.

989
00:50:48.436 --> 00:50:51.134
I'm sorry, Mom. I shouldn't have run away.

990
00:50:51.136 --> 00:50:52.668
And I should've told you the truth.

991
00:50:52.670 --> 00:50:55.535
There's a hundred agents in
the forest looking for Dad.

992
00:50:55.537 --> 00:50:57.835
Adam, shh, watch what you say.

993
00:50:57.837 --> 00:50:59.535
Don't worry, they'll never find him.

994
00:50:59.537 --> 00:51:02.634
He's hiding in the tunnels
near the base of the waterfall.

995
00:51:02.636 --> 00:51:04.836
Hmm. (CHUCKLES SOFTLY)

996
00:51:04.838 --> 00:51:07.069
This is an all-call.

997
00:51:07.071 --> 00:51:11.303
All agents re-route to sector G16.

998
00:51:11.305 --> 00:51:16.970
<i>I repeat, the prize is
in G16. I'm on my way.</i>

999
00:51:16.972 --> 00:51:21.702
You heard the man, turn
it around. Double time.

1000
00:51:21.704 --> 00:51:25.105
The bigfoot is hiding down there.

1001
00:51:28.707 --> 00:51:31.205
What are you waiting for? Get down there!

1002
00:51:31.207 --> 00:51:32.803
I hear something.

1003
00:51:32.805 --> 00:51:35.138
What is it?

1004
00:51:35.140 --> 00:51:36.873
(YELLING)

1005
00:51:39.839 --> 00:51:40.841
(GRUNTS)

1006
00:51:43.441 --> 00:51:45.172
(SIGHS)

1007
00:51:45.174 --> 00:51:47.705
(LAUGHS) Someone push you in the pool?

1008
00:51:47.707 --> 00:51:50.339
Adam! Don't hurt him! Please!

1009
00:51:50.341 --> 00:51:52.806
Take her home. The boy rides with me.

1010
00:51:52.808 --> 00:51:54.374
Where are you taking him?

1011
00:51:54.376 --> 00:51:57.539
Don't worry, we'll be right behind you.

1012
00:51:57.541 --> 00:52:00.376
We're going to have a little chat.

1013
00:52:01.141 --> 00:52:03.175
(ENGINES STARTING)

1014
00:52:16.542 --> 00:52:18.244
(ADAM GRUNTING)

1015
00:52:20.378 --> 00:52:23.476
One last chance. Where is your father?

1016
00:52:23.478 --> 00:52:25.507
So you can lock him in a cage?

1017
00:52:25.509 --> 00:52:28.743
Your father's DNA can
help millions of people.

1018
00:52:28.745 --> 00:52:32.876
People who just want a
full head of healthy hair.

1019
00:52:32.878 --> 00:52:35.643
So you just take some DNA and let him go?

1020
00:52:35.645 --> 00:52:38.709
Not exactly. We'll be partners.

1021
00:52:38.711 --> 00:52:41.977
Your dad will work exclusively for us.

1022
00:52:41.979 --> 00:52:43.443
Give me a break.

1023
00:52:43.445 --> 00:52:44.878
Adam, listen to me...

1024
00:52:44.880 --> 00:52:47.045
He's not a lab rat. He's my dad!

1025
00:52:47.047 --> 00:52:48.047
(SIGHS)

1026
00:52:50.479 --> 00:52:55.215
It's becoming clear to me that you
have no interest in negotiating.

1027
00:52:56.013 --> 00:52:57.846
<i>Light it up, boys.</i>

1028
00:53:02.546 --> 00:53:04.312
Are you crazy?

1029
00:53:04.314 --> 00:53:09.113
Crazy is such an ugly
word. I prefer "motivated."

1030
00:53:09.115 --> 00:53:11.412
You'll never catch him. There's
too much forest out there.

1031
00:53:11.414 --> 00:53:15.781
(LAUGHS) Oh, my boy, the fire's
not for him. It's for you.

1032
00:53:17.148 --> 00:53:18.615
(HUMMING)

1033
00:53:23.015 --> 00:53:24.913
Nice doing business with you.

1034
00:53:24.915 --> 00:53:26.146
No!

1035
00:53:26.148 --> 00:53:27.679
(EASTMAN LAUGHING)

1036
00:53:27.681 --> 00:53:29.583
Oh. (PANTING)

1037
00:53:48.618 --> 00:53:49.585
(GASPS)

1038
00:53:50.484 --> 00:53:52.251
Help! Help me!

1039
00:54:00.785 --> 00:54:02.186
(COUGHING)

1040
00:54:09.220 --> 00:54:10.819
(GRUNTING)

1041
00:54:11.452 --> 00:54:12.420
Dad!

1042
00:54:12.920 --> 00:54:14.221
Hang on!

1043
00:54:15.353 --> 00:54:16.588
(GRUNTS)

1044
00:54:17.420 --> 00:54:18.421
(GASPS)

1045
00:54:21.753 --> 00:54:22.787
No!

1046
00:54:24.587 --> 00:54:27.085
(SCOFFS) So predictable.

1047
00:54:27.087 --> 00:54:29.755
Dad. Come on. Please.

1048
00:54:33.755 --> 00:54:34.755
(YELPS)

1049
00:54:40.321 --> 00:54:41.289
(GROWLS)

1050
00:54:45.555 --> 00:54:46.556
(ADAM COUGHING)

1051
00:54:46.889 --> 00:54:47.890
Dad!

1052
00:54:50.156 --> 00:54:51.157
(HELICOPTER BLADES WHIRRING)

1053
00:54:59.656 --> 00:55:02.523
Mission accomplished. So long!

1054
00:55:04.523 --> 00:55:06.226
(GROWLING)

1055
00:55:13.323 --> 00:55:14.757
BIGFOOT: Wake up, Adam.

1056
00:55:18.525 --> 00:55:19.726
Wake up.

1057
00:55:20.193 --> 00:55:21.589
Dad?

1058
00:55:21.591 --> 00:55:24.257
He's awake. Are you okay?

1059
00:55:24.259 --> 00:55:26.657
I... I think so.

1060
00:55:26.659 --> 00:55:29.825
All right, then. Take
care of yourself, kid.

1061
00:55:29.827 --> 00:55:31.825
Wait, where are you going?

1062
00:55:31.827 --> 00:55:34.225
To find a new place to start over.

1063
00:55:34.227 --> 00:55:35.424
You're just going to leave?

1064
00:55:35.426 --> 00:55:37.357
Well, not much left here for us, is there?

1065
00:55:37.359 --> 00:55:38.360
Way to go, man.

1066
00:55:44.327 --> 00:55:46.062
Hey! Wait.

1067
00:55:47.228 --> 00:55:48.658
Stop.

1068
00:55:48.660 --> 00:55:49.728
(GRUNTS)

1069
00:55:50.727 --> 00:55:52.625
Hey, I said stop!

1070
00:55:52.627 --> 00:55:54.095
(ROARS)

1071
00:55:54.695 --> 00:55:56.095
(YELLS)

1072
00:55:56.729 --> 00:55:58.127
Huh?

1073
00:55:58.129 --> 00:56:00.060
If you're going to bite my head off, do it.

1074
00:56:00.062 --> 00:56:01.828
Otherwise, I've got something to say.

1075
00:56:04.294 --> 00:56:07.028
I've got a plan but I need your help.

1076
00:56:07.030 --> 00:56:09.362
It's your problem, not ours.

1077
00:56:10.997 --> 00:56:13.827
This isn't about me, it's about my dad.

1078
00:56:13.829 --> 00:56:16.728
I made the mistake, he
shouldn't have to pay for it.

1079
00:56:16.730 --> 00:56:20.163
So you want us to bail you out now? Nice.

1080
00:56:20.165 --> 00:56:22.029
I didn't mean for this to happen.

1081
00:56:22.031 --> 00:56:25.327
I just came out here to
find my family. I'm sorry.

1082
00:56:25.329 --> 00:56:28.162
Sorry isn't going to
unburn down our forest!

1083
00:56:28.164 --> 00:56:32.163
If I could take it back,
I would. But I can't.

1084
00:56:32.165 --> 00:56:34.495
Please, guys, I need your help.

1085
00:56:34.497 --> 00:56:36.928
When animals go up against humans,

1086
00:56:36.930 --> 00:56:38.828
humans always win.

1087
00:56:38.830 --> 00:56:41.897
I'm not gonna end up a bearskin rug.

1088
00:56:41.899 --> 00:56:44.564
What would Bigfoot do
if you were in trouble?

1089
00:56:44.566 --> 00:56:46.197
Would he just walk away?

1090
00:56:46.199 --> 00:56:48.730
Sometimes doing the right thing is hard.

1091
00:56:48.732 --> 00:56:51.796
I'm not going to tell
you it won't be dangerous.

1092
00:56:51.798 --> 00:56:54.665
But the only way we stand a
chance is if we work together.

1093
00:56:54.667 --> 00:56:57.534
Please, Bigfoot needs your help.

1094
00:56:59.201 --> 00:57:02.563
The kid's right. Bigfoot needs us.

1095
00:57:02.565 --> 00:57:05.200
I agree with them, I'm in.

1096
00:57:05.201 --> 00:57:07.731
All right then, we're in.

1097
00:57:07.733 --> 00:57:10.565
Whoa, wait, we're not
even going to discuss it?

1098
00:57:10.567 --> 00:57:14.866
Uh, I was going to say "in"
too, you just said it first.

1099
00:57:14.868 --> 00:57:16.867
What do you say, Wilbur?

1100
00:57:19.367 --> 00:57:21.200
Hmm, okay.

1101
00:57:21.202 --> 00:57:23.136
Let's do it for Bigfoot.

1102
00:57:40.269 --> 00:57:42.835
EASTMAN: (LAUGHING) I
could watch that all day.

1103
00:57:42.837 --> 00:57:44.634
It's incredible.

1104
00:57:44.636 --> 00:57:48.534
The structure of the hair is
different at the molecular level.

1105
00:57:48.536 --> 00:57:49.837
(BIGFOOT YAWNS)

1106
00:57:50.871 --> 00:57:53.236
Oh. Oh! It's awake.

1107
00:57:53.238 --> 00:57:55.970
Ah, good morning, my dear beast.

1108
00:57:55.972 --> 00:57:59.803
Or should I say... Doctor Harrison?

1109
00:57:59.805 --> 00:58:01.736
(GRUNTING) Let me go!

1110
00:58:01.738 --> 00:58:03.339
Ah, ah, ah. Calm down.

1111
00:58:03.904 --> 00:58:05.606
(GRUNTING)

1112
00:58:06.672 --> 00:58:08.204
Or not.

1113
00:58:08.206 --> 00:58:09.440
Get back!

1114
00:58:11.372 --> 00:58:13.536
Oh, no, no, no. There's no need for that.

1115
00:58:13.538 --> 00:58:17.237
Do you have any idea what that thing costs?

1116
00:58:17.239 --> 00:58:19.904
(SCOFFS) I'm sure we've got another one.

1117
00:58:19.906 --> 00:58:23.237
Ah, the benefits of being rich.

1118
00:58:23.239 --> 00:58:26.773
This thing here, I have no idea what it is.

1119
00:58:29.841 --> 00:58:32.405
But we'll replace it too.

1120
00:58:32.407 --> 00:58:35.873
The only thing of value
here is our new friend.

1121
00:58:35.875 --> 00:58:38.072
You'll never get what you want from me.

1122
00:58:38.074 --> 00:58:40.906
I'll fight you every step of the way.

1123
00:58:40.908 --> 00:58:43.075
(LAUGHS) No, you won't.

1124
00:58:43.077 --> 00:58:44.874
You want to know how I know?

1125
00:58:44.876 --> 00:58:46.876
Your family is still out there.

1126
00:58:47.942 --> 00:58:49.708
(GRUNTS) Leave them out of this.

1127
00:58:49.710 --> 00:58:51.673
Happily. I have no use for them.

1128
00:58:51.675 --> 00:58:54.042
But if you make life hard for us,

1129
00:58:54.044 --> 00:58:56.908
we can make life very hard for them.

1130
00:58:56.910 --> 00:59:00.308
- That said, if you cooperate...
- (GRUNTING)

1131
00:59:00.310 --> 00:59:03.508
I promise to take good care of your family.

1132
00:59:03.510 --> 00:59:06.511
So, Mr. Bigfoot, what will it be?

1133
00:59:07.678 --> 00:59:08.945
(GRUNTING)

1134
00:59:13.044 --> 00:59:15.508
Well, guys, it looks like we're
going to have to hitch a ride.

1135
00:59:15.510 --> 00:59:16.576
Got it.

1136
00:59:16.578 --> 00:59:17.879
(PANTING)

1137
00:59:19.145 --> 00:59:21.543
- What?
- More of a covert ride.

1138
00:59:21.545 --> 00:59:24.344
Got it.

1139
00:59:24.346 --> 00:59:27.910
Okay, we'll wait for the last
trailer in the convoy. Everyone ready?

1140
00:59:27.912 --> 00:59:29.209
I was born ready.

1141
00:59:29.211 --> 00:59:31.010
Actually, I was born a few weeks early.

1142
00:59:31.012 --> 00:59:32.444
I needed a lot of help to get started...

1143
00:59:32.446 --> 00:59:34.078
- Shut up.
- Will you shut up?

1144
00:59:34.080 --> 00:59:35.376
- Shut up.
- STEVE: Yeah.

1145
00:59:35.378 --> 00:59:36.544
What?

1146
00:59:36.546 --> 00:59:38.877
Okay, guys, it's now or never.

1147
00:59:38.879 --> 00:59:40.777
(SIGHS) Are you sure about this?

1148
00:59:40.779 --> 00:59:41.880
Now.

1149
00:59:45.414 --> 00:59:47.615
(SIGHS) This is nuts. Whoa!

1150
00:59:49.747 --> 00:59:50.748
Whoa!

1151
00:59:51.280 --> 00:59:52.281
(GASPS)

1152
00:59:58.181 --> 01:00:00.047
Wait! Hold on!

1153
01:00:00.580 --> 01:00:01.879
Wilbur! Run!

1154
01:00:01.881 --> 01:00:03.582
What do you think I'm doing?

1155
01:00:07.081 --> 01:00:08.082
(GRUNTS)

1156
01:00:12.715 --> 01:00:14.713
Whoa, what was that?

1157
01:00:14.715 --> 01:00:15.980
Why you don't y'all go check it out?

1158
01:00:15.982 --> 01:00:18.714
Aw, why do I have to
go? I'm covered in latte!

1159
01:00:18.716 --> 01:00:21.548
(LAUGHS) You're drinking a latte?

1160
01:00:21.550 --> 01:00:23.050
What's wrong with that?

1161
01:00:24.250 --> 01:00:26.550
(SIGHS) Fine. Let's both go.

1162
01:00:29.918 --> 01:00:31.015
Hmm.

1163
01:00:31.017 --> 01:00:33.252
All right, let's roll.

1164
01:00:39.951 --> 01:00:43.283
Hang on tight, guys. This
is going to be a long ride.

1165
01:00:43.285 --> 01:00:46.051
(CHUCKLES) Check out Steve. He's loving it.

1166
01:00:50.418 --> 01:00:53.583
(WHOOPS) This is amazing.

1167
01:00:53.585 --> 01:00:54.851
(ADAM LAUGHING)

1168
01:00:54.853 --> 01:00:56.219
He probably got tired
of pecking for a living.

1169
01:00:58.552 --> 01:01:00.584
I've extracted the bigfoot DNA

1170
01:01:00.586 --> 01:01:02.551
and spliced it into the sequence.

1171
01:01:02.553 --> 01:01:04.383
So what are you waiting for?

1172
01:01:04.385 --> 01:01:07.252
This needs to be tested immediately.

1173
01:01:07.254 --> 01:01:08.888
Send in the intern.

1174
01:01:10.253 --> 01:01:11.819
(GRUNTS)

1175
01:01:11.821 --> 01:01:14.185
Uh, Dr. Billingsley? Hi.

1176
01:01:14.187 --> 01:01:16.352
I... I don't mean to bother you,

1177
01:01:16.354 --> 01:01:19.886
but I really need you
to sign my time sheet...

1178
01:01:19.888 --> 01:01:21.853
No, not again!

1179
01:01:21.855 --> 01:01:27.586
Ouch! I need to really
call my academic adviser.

1180
01:01:27.588 --> 01:01:29.222
(SIGHS)

1181
01:01:30.556 --> 01:01:32.021
Hmm.

1182
01:01:32.023 --> 01:01:34.787
Oh. Oh! What's going on?

1183
01:01:34.789 --> 01:01:38.089
My hair, it's growing. (CHUCKLES)

1184
01:01:38.589 --> 01:01:39.889
(LAUGHING)

1185
01:01:43.923 --> 01:01:45.257
(MUSIC PLAYING)

1186
01:01:46.590 --> 01:01:48.354
Incredible!

1187
01:01:48.356 --> 01:01:51.555
It will be, but I'm still
fine-tuning the genetic sequence.

1188
01:01:51.557 --> 01:01:54.555
We're close, but I need
more time with Bigfoot.

1189
01:01:54.557 --> 01:01:56.722
EASTMAN: We're closer than we've ever been.

1190
01:01:56.724 --> 01:01:58.689
I want you working around the clock.

1191
01:01:58.691 --> 01:02:02.758
Nobody rests and nobody goes home
until we've cracked this thing.

1192
01:02:03.525 --> 01:02:05.591
INTERN: (GRUNTS) Sir?

1193
01:02:14.727 --> 01:02:17.156
Greg. Gerry. What's new with you guys?

1194
01:02:17.158 --> 01:02:19.090
(CHUCKLES) This guy drinks lattes.

1195
01:02:19.092 --> 01:02:22.091
- Oh, come on. You promised to let it go.
- (LAUGHING)

1196
01:02:22.093 --> 01:02:24.260
GATE GUARD:
Well, lah-di-dah.

1197
01:02:36.295 --> 01:02:38.892
Ah! Are you kidding me?

1198
01:02:38.894 --> 01:02:40.561
(CHUCKLES)

1199
01:02:42.562 --> 01:02:46.060
How are we going to find
him? This place is gigantic!

1200
01:02:46.062 --> 01:02:48.295
Shh. Let me concentrate.

1201
01:03:02.529 --> 01:03:05.694
EASTMAN: How much time do you
need to finish sequencing his DNA?

1202
01:03:05.696 --> 01:03:07.430
BILLINGSLEY: The ongoing mutations are...

1203
01:03:09.497 --> 01:03:12.329
I can't see him. We've got to get closer.

1204
01:03:12.331 --> 01:03:14.329
Steve, take out those security cameras.

1205
01:03:14.331 --> 01:03:15.395
I'm on it.

1206
01:03:15.397 --> 01:03:17.598
Everyone else, come with me.

1207
01:03:30.699 --> 01:03:31.929
(BEEPING)

1208
01:03:31.931 --> 01:03:33.633
GUARD: Piece of junk!

1209
01:03:35.700 --> 01:03:36.666
(WHIMPERING)

1210
01:03:44.199 --> 01:03:45.467
Hmm.

1211
01:03:53.899 --> 01:03:54.901
- (TAPPING)
- (GLASS BREAKINGP)

1212
01:03:58.769 --> 01:04:00.466
TECH SUPPORT OPERATOR ON PHONE: <i>Sir?</i>

1213
01:04:00.468 --> 01:04:02.767
Yeah, tech support? There's
something wrong with the system here.

1214
01:04:02.769 --> 01:04:04.665
All the monitors are on the fritz.

1215
01:04:04.667 --> 01:04:07.267
<i>Have you checked if
they are all plugged in?</i>

1216
01:04:07.269 --> 01:04:08.702
Of course they're plugged in!

1217
01:04:10.168 --> 01:04:11.899
What do you say we smash it down?

1218
01:04:11.901 --> 01:04:13.933
Stealth all the way.

1219
01:04:13.935 --> 01:04:18.199
Step aside, kid. Let a
professional show you how it's done.

1220
01:04:18.201 --> 01:04:19.701
Where'd you get that mask?

1221
01:04:19.703 --> 01:04:22.766
Girl, there's a lot
you don't know about me.

1222
01:04:22.768 --> 01:04:26.703
Lick, stick, and cut.

1223
01:04:29.436 --> 01:04:31.168
(CHUCKLES)

1224
01:04:31.170 --> 01:04:32.372
Oh, shoot.

1225
01:04:36.936 --> 01:04:40.601
We've got a perimeter breach!

1226
01:04:40.603 --> 01:04:44.470
The wrong thing to do here would
be to start pointing fingers.

1227
01:04:44.472 --> 01:04:47.070
Careful... Careful... There's
broken glass everywhere.

1228
01:04:47.072 --> 01:04:49.269
TECH SUPPORT OPERATOR: <i>This is
standard troubleshooting procedure.</i>

1229
01:04:49.271 --> 01:04:52.069
<i>Ninety percent of the time,
something is unplugged.</i>

1230
01:04:52.071 --> 01:04:55.970
Like I said, everything is plugged in!

1231
01:04:55.972 --> 01:04:58.104
(BANGING)

1232
01:04:58.106 --> 01:04:59.641
(GASPS)

1233
01:05:00.905 --> 01:05:04.203
Help! Tech support!
Get down here right now!

1234
01:05:04.205 --> 01:05:07.641
<i>I'm so sorry, sir, I am in
India. There is nothing I can do.</i>

1235
01:05:09.241 --> 01:05:10.540
(ROARS)

1236
01:05:12.073 --> 01:05:14.371
<i>Have I been helpful for you today?</i>

1237
01:05:14.373 --> 01:05:16.274
<i>Would you be willing
to take a short survey?</i>

1238
01:05:18.039 --> 01:05:19.074
ADAM: There he is.

1239
01:05:21.041 --> 01:05:22.838
We'll have to go through that door.

1240
01:05:22.840 --> 01:05:24.308
Watch out, Wilbur, they're coming in!

1241
01:05:26.874 --> 01:05:28.673
Don't worry. I got it.

1242
01:05:28.675 --> 01:05:31.873
What are we gonna do?
How do we get out of here?

1243
01:05:31.875 --> 01:05:34.007
Check the lockers for anything we can use.

1244
01:05:34.009 --> 01:05:35.573
Take whatever you can carry.

1245
01:05:35.575 --> 01:05:38.076
I need more men. Get them down here now!

1246
01:05:40.043 --> 01:05:43.275
Jackpot! Does it make me look cool?

1247
01:05:43.277 --> 01:05:46.576
Hey, no fair! I want the
flare gun! Me, me, me me, me!

1248
01:05:46.578 --> 01:05:47.909
Fine, take it.

1249
01:05:48.476 --> 01:05:49.477
(GIGGLES)

1250
01:05:50.743 --> 01:05:51.744
(GROANS)

1251
01:05:54.043 --> 01:05:55.745
(GROANS) What?

1252
01:05:57.710 --> 01:05:58.677
(ROARS)

1253
01:06:00.977 --> 01:06:02.142
What?

1254
01:06:02.144 --> 01:06:04.478
Maybe we should try something else.

1255
01:06:05.943 --> 01:06:07.909
Yeah, that's more like it!

1256
01:06:07.911 --> 01:06:09.276
(GRUNTING)

1257
01:06:09.278 --> 01:06:12.145
Ow! Watch where you're swinging that thing!

1258
01:06:14.844 --> 01:06:16.042
On three.

1259
01:06:16.044 --> 01:06:17.943
Okay, guys. It's now or never.

1260
01:06:17.945 --> 01:06:19.211
Okay.

1261
01:06:19.213 --> 01:06:20.380
One...

1262
01:06:21.113 --> 01:06:22.545
Two...

1263
01:06:22.547 --> 01:06:23.547
(EXCLAIMS)

1264
01:06:24.045 --> 01:06:25.046
Three!

1265
01:06:29.179 --> 01:06:30.146
Fire. Fire!

1266
01:06:32.881 --> 01:06:34.814
Keep firing! Keep... Oh!

1267
01:06:41.547 --> 01:06:43.113
Gotcha, you little weasel.

1268
01:06:43.115 --> 01:06:45.648
Why don't you pick on
somebody your own size?

1269
01:06:49.747 --> 01:06:52.147
Bring it on, suckers!

1270
01:06:52.149 --> 01:06:53.283
(GRUNTING)

1271
01:06:55.882 --> 01:06:56.849
Ha!

1272
01:06:58.450 --> 01:06:59.450
(LAUGHS) Oh...

1273
01:07:02.815 --> 01:07:03.816
No!

1274
01:07:04.648 --> 01:07:06.915
Get your hands off him.

1275
01:07:08.984 --> 01:07:10.318
(PANTING)

1276
01:07:14.183 --> 01:07:15.881
What now?

1277
01:07:15.883 --> 01:07:19.551
I'll deal with them. You go
find your dad. Go, Adam, go.

1278
01:07:19.950 --> 01:07:21.218
(ROARS)

1279
01:07:30.417 --> 01:07:31.452
Over there.

1280
01:07:34.885 --> 01:07:35.986
(PANTING)

1281
01:07:53.920 --> 01:07:54.920
Come on, Captain!

1282
01:07:57.487 --> 01:07:58.587
(GRUNTING)

1283
01:08:01.786 --> 01:08:02.787
Over there!

1284
01:08:08.987 --> 01:08:10.087
(BEEPING)

1285
01:08:10.089 --> 01:08:11.287
Huh?

1286
01:08:11.289 --> 01:08:13.121
Whoa, get off me.

1287
01:08:13.123 --> 01:08:14.123
(GRUNTS)

1288
01:08:18.389 --> 01:08:21.120
Hey, Wilbur, get me up there!

1289
01:08:21.122 --> 01:08:23.788
My pleasure. Whoa!

1290
01:08:23.790 --> 01:08:24.790
(SPUTTERS)

1291
01:08:26.722 --> 01:08:29.156
Yee haw!

1292
01:08:31.357 --> 01:08:32.688
(GRUNTS)

1293
01:08:32.690 --> 01:08:33.957
(ELECTRICITY CRACKLING)

1294
01:08:38.190 --> 01:08:39.587
Whoo-hoo!

1295
01:08:39.589 --> 01:08:40.787
(GRUNTS)

1296
01:08:40.789 --> 01:08:41.888
- GUARD: Don't move!
- What?

1297
01:08:41.890 --> 01:08:43.021
You're under arrest.

1298
01:08:43.023 --> 01:08:44.824
Y'all got to read me my rights.

1299
01:08:45.958 --> 01:08:46.959
(GRUNTING)

1300
01:08:48.326 --> 01:08:50.323
That is one tough bear.

1301
01:08:50.325 --> 01:08:51.959
(PANTING)

1302
01:08:53.259 --> 01:08:54.358
Oh!

1303
01:09:03.160 --> 01:09:04.425
Dad!

1304
01:09:04.427 --> 01:09:06.057
Adam, how did you get in here?

1305
01:09:06.059 --> 01:09:09.325
Long story, but don't worry,
I am here to get you out.

1306
01:09:09.327 --> 01:09:10.992
It's going to be okay, Adam.

1307
01:09:10.994 --> 01:09:12.259
What are you doing?

1308
01:09:12.261 --> 01:09:14.591
Everything I did was to keep you safe.

1309
01:09:14.593 --> 01:09:17.757
Not a day went by that I
didn't wish I was in your life.

1310
01:09:17.759 --> 01:09:19.559
We've got to hurry. Come on!

1311
01:09:19.561 --> 01:09:21.759
I need you to believe that.

1312
01:09:21.761 --> 01:09:24.059
You've been a naughty, naughty boy, Adam.

1313
01:09:24.061 --> 01:09:26.759
It's very lucky your
father is a friend of mine,

1314
01:09:26.761 --> 01:09:29.725
and friends forgive and forget.

1315
01:09:29.727 --> 01:09:31.727
You're going to have to catch us first.

1316
01:09:31.729 --> 01:09:33.128
Come on, Dad. Let's run!

1317
01:09:33.130 --> 01:09:34.626
I'm not going with you.

1318
01:09:34.628 --> 01:09:36.393
What?

1319
01:09:36.395 --> 01:09:40.394
I'm staying here. You and your
mother are going to be safe.

1320
01:09:40.396 --> 01:09:42.128
It's better this way.

1321
01:09:42.130 --> 01:09:43.593
What did you do to him?

1322
01:09:43.595 --> 01:09:45.561
He's sick. You're killing him!

1323
01:09:45.563 --> 01:09:49.893
He's here under his own free
will. He can leave at any time.

1324
01:09:49.895 --> 01:09:51.796
(WEAKLY) I'll be fine. Just go, Adam.

1325
01:09:52.730 --> 01:09:54.460
Don't look so surprised,

1326
01:09:54.462 --> 01:09:56.995
we're partners, your dad and I.

1327
01:09:56.997 --> 01:09:59.128
- I told you we would be.
- Go on, now.

1328
01:09:59.130 --> 01:10:02.163
No! I'm not leaving without you. (GROANS)

1329
01:10:02.165 --> 01:10:04.263
You promised not to hurt him!

1330
01:10:04.265 --> 01:10:06.299
Hmm. Treat our young guest gently.

1331
01:10:08.499 --> 01:10:11.596
It's time for Daddy to get back to work.

1332
01:10:11.598 --> 01:10:12.999
Take care of your mother.

1333
01:10:21.300 --> 01:10:22.566
Hmm.

1334
01:10:28.033 --> 01:10:30.396
(GROANING)

1335
01:10:30.398 --> 01:10:34.066
(SLURRING) I had the most beautiful dream.

1336
01:10:34.068 --> 01:10:36.398
I could take the rings off my tail

1337
01:10:36.400 --> 01:10:40.031
and link them together
like a fancy magician.

1338
01:10:40.033 --> 01:10:41.765
(SLURRING) I could be your assistant.

1339
01:10:41.767 --> 01:10:45.432
You could saw me in
half, quarters, pennies,

1340
01:10:45.434 --> 01:10:46.699
whatever spare change you like...

1341
01:10:46.701 --> 01:10:48.933
Whoa, how many darts did you guys have?

1342
01:10:48.935 --> 01:10:52.465
Let's just say that I was over my limit.

1343
01:10:52.467 --> 01:10:55.632
EASTMAN: You'll never have
to worry about anything again.

1344
01:10:55.634 --> 01:10:59.304
Take it from me, you're
going to love being rich.

1345
01:10:59.736 --> 01:11:02.068
(CHUCKLES)

1346
01:11:02.070 --> 01:11:07.166
Oh, man, the kid sold us out.
He took the money and ran.

1347
01:11:07.168 --> 01:11:11.069
Just think of it like he's
away on a business trip,

1348
01:11:11.071 --> 01:11:13.567
working hard to provide for you.

1349
01:11:13.569 --> 01:11:16.334
Except he never comes home
from this business trip.

1350
01:11:16.336 --> 01:11:20.203
Oh, your father is a busy
man. You know how it is.

1351
01:11:20.205 --> 01:11:22.768
Well, business is business, I guess.

1352
01:11:22.770 --> 01:11:23.904
That a boy.

1353
01:11:24.305 --> 01:11:25.569
Huh?

1354
01:11:25.571 --> 01:11:28.036
- Stop him! Get the boy.
- (ALARM BLARING)

1355
01:11:28.038 --> 01:11:30.239
(LAUGHS) Business is business!

1356
01:11:31.437 --> 01:11:32.439
(GRUNTS)

1357
01:11:34.405 --> 01:11:35.438
Huh?

1358
01:11:37.538 --> 01:11:41.136
- Don't let it get wet!
- My beautiful hair!

1359
01:11:41.138 --> 01:11:43.036
Ah! My toupee!

1360
01:11:43.038 --> 01:11:44.308
(BOTH SCREAMING)

1361
01:11:46.640 --> 01:11:53.637
Security! Security! Shut down the fire
alarm in sector 4 and open the doors!

1362
01:11:53.639 --> 01:11:58.106
<i>Security, shut down the
fire alarm in sector 4.</i>

1363
01:11:58.108 --> 01:11:59.272
What?

1364
01:11:59.274 --> 01:12:01.208
A... A fire? Oh, no.

1365
01:12:05.606 --> 01:12:07.005
(ALARM BLARING)

1366
01:12:07.007 --> 01:12:08.906
AUTOMATED VOICE ON PA SYSTEM:
<i>Evacuate! Evacuate!</i>

1367
01:12:08.908 --> 01:12:12.272
<i>Please proceed to your nearest
exit in an orderly manner.</i>

1368
01:12:12.274 --> 01:12:14.573
What's wrong with that guy?

1369
01:12:14.575 --> 01:12:18.840
Security, security. Switch
off the alarm right away!

1370
01:12:18.842 --> 01:12:20.940
AUTOMATED VOICE ON PA SYSTEM:
<i>Evacuate. Evacuate.</i>

1371
01:12:20.942 --> 01:12:22.374
(ALL YELLING)

1372
01:12:22.376 --> 01:12:26.108
Stop it, stop it, this is a false alarm.

1373
01:12:26.110 --> 01:12:27.908
AUTOMATED VOICE ON PA SYSTEM:
<i>This is not a drill.</i>

1374
01:12:27.910 --> 01:12:30.573
<i>Please exit the facility at once.</i>

1375
01:12:30.575 --> 01:12:31.975
What are you doing?

1376
01:12:31.977 --> 01:12:33.075
Standard procedure, sir.

1377
01:12:33.077 --> 01:12:35.444
Let me... Argh! ...go!

1378
01:12:41.211 --> 01:12:44.909
Oh, look who's back.
Mister sellout moneybags.

1379
01:12:44.911 --> 01:12:46.875
Did you really think I'd leave you here?

1380
01:12:46.877 --> 01:12:48.043
Hmm.

1381
01:12:48.045 --> 01:12:49.341
(BEEPING)

1382
01:12:49.343 --> 01:12:50.576
Get these cages open now. Everybody out.

1383
01:12:50.578 --> 01:12:52.742
- TINA: Yeah.
- (GIGGLES)

1384
01:12:52.744 --> 01:12:54.779
Feel free to start with me.

1385
01:12:55.644 --> 01:12:56.645
(WILBUR GROANING)

1386
01:13:00.012 --> 01:13:02.644
I can't believe you're unlocking
all these randoms before me!

1387
01:13:02.646 --> 01:13:04.277
Thank you, my dear.

1388
01:13:04.279 --> 01:13:07.011
Mmm. Hello there, cowboy.

1389
01:13:07.013 --> 01:13:08.013
What are you in for?

1390
01:13:08.547 --> 01:13:09.646
Murder.

1391
01:13:10.979 --> 01:13:12.845
Just joking. I eat carrots.

1392
01:13:12.847 --> 01:13:14.947
(LAUGHING) You're funny.

1393
01:13:16.813 --> 01:13:18.144
(LAUGHING)

1394
01:13:18.146 --> 01:13:20.277
Tina! Get me out of here!

1395
01:13:20.279 --> 01:13:23.148
This is not the time for
fraternizing with inmates!

1396
01:13:25.547 --> 01:13:26.878
Adam, what are you doing?

1397
01:13:26.880 --> 01:13:28.912
Come on, Dad, I'm breaking you out.

1398
01:13:28.914 --> 01:13:33.880
I told you, I can't go. They'll always
be after me. We'll always be hiding.

1399
01:13:33.882 --> 01:13:36.080
I don't care, as long as we're together.

1400
01:13:36.082 --> 01:13:40.579
No, I won't do that to
you. I'm not leaving.

1401
01:13:40.581 --> 01:13:44.080
If you don't come with me, I'll
tell them I'm a bigfoot too.

1402
01:13:44.082 --> 01:13:46.082
You can't.

1403
01:13:46.084 --> 01:13:49.048
I've got your genes, I've got your crazy
hair. I've got everything they need.

1404
01:13:49.050 --> 01:13:50.114
Adam, no.

1405
01:13:50.116 --> 01:13:52.647
Either we both stay, or we both go.

1406
01:13:52.649 --> 01:13:54.381
It's up to you.

1407
01:13:54.383 --> 01:13:57.651
But I need my dad, and I'm
not leaving here without you.

1408
01:13:58.151 --> 01:13:59.451
(SIGHS)

1409
01:14:00.983 --> 01:14:03.617
You are one stubborn kid.

1410
01:14:05.584 --> 01:14:08.384
(CHUCKLES) I guess I take after my old man.

1411
01:14:12.351 --> 01:14:15.516
Where's Adam? You said
he was right behind us.

1412
01:14:15.518 --> 01:14:17.849
What have you done with my son?

1413
01:14:17.851 --> 01:14:19.949
Calm down, he's on the way.

1414
01:14:19.951 --> 01:14:21.518
As soon as he gets home,
we'll be out of your hair.

1415
01:14:21.520 --> 01:14:24.316
As soon as you leave, I'm calling the cops.

1416
01:14:24.318 --> 01:14:26.617
(LAUGHS) What are you gonna say?

1417
01:14:26.619 --> 01:14:29.051
"Hello, police? My husband is Bigfoot,

1418
01:14:29.053 --> 01:14:31.118
"and he's been captured
in an evil conspiracy."

1419
01:14:31.120 --> 01:14:33.384
Sounds pretty crazy to me.

1420
01:14:33.386 --> 01:14:35.651
You know, someone with a story like that

1421
01:14:35.653 --> 01:14:37.785
probably isn't fit to raise a kid.

1422
01:14:37.787 --> 01:14:40.551
How dare you. You should
be ashamed of yourself.

1423
01:14:40.553 --> 01:14:43.217
Listen, lady, we're just doing our jobs.

1424
01:14:43.219 --> 01:14:44.651
(SCOFFS)

1425
01:14:44.653 --> 01:14:47.553
Now where's the can? You
got a bathroom in this place?

1426
01:14:47.555 --> 01:14:49.955
No, we go in the bushes outside.

1427
01:14:51.121 --> 01:14:52.622
It's upstairs.

1428
01:14:59.621 --> 01:15:02.454
GARCIA: Simpson! Come into
the bathroom, right now!

1429
01:15:02.456 --> 01:15:06.152
Uh... That's okay, I'll
wait until you're done.

1430
01:15:06.154 --> 01:15:07.855
Would you get in here?

1431
01:15:10.089 --> 01:15:11.823
What's going on?

1432
01:15:15.422 --> 01:15:17.088
Sir, we're at the house.

1433
01:15:17.090 --> 01:15:19.653
The boy's a bigfoot. We've
got the hair to prove it.

1434
01:15:19.655 --> 01:15:22.822
EASTMAN: (EXCITEDLY) <i>What?
Fantastic! Change of plan, then.</i>

1435
01:15:22.824 --> 01:15:24.490
Roger that.

1436
01:15:32.724 --> 01:15:34.523
(GRUNTS)

1437
01:15:34.525 --> 01:15:38.623
That's not very nice. Do you
treat all your guests like this?

1438
01:15:38.625 --> 01:15:41.057
Just the ones that kidnap my son.

1439
01:15:41.059 --> 01:15:42.626
(SCREAMING)

1440
01:15:46.225 --> 01:15:48.890
AUTOMATED VOICE ON PA SYSTEM:
<i>Evacuate, evacuate.</i>

1441
01:15:48.892 --> 01:15:51.424
<i>Time to get your butts in gear.</i>

1442
01:15:51.426 --> 01:15:53.957
<i>Evacuate! Evacuate!</i>

1443
01:15:53.959 --> 01:15:54.959
(GRUNTS)

1444
01:15:56.059 --> 01:15:57.694
(EVACUATION ORDERS CONTINUE)

1445
01:15:58.459 --> 01:15:59.794
Follow me, buddy.

1446
01:16:03.293 --> 01:16:07.161
No more hiding. We're shutting
this place down for good.

1447
01:16:08.593 --> 01:16:10.029
(GRUNTS)

1448
01:16:21.328 --> 01:16:23.626
(BEEPING)

1449
01:16:23.628 --> 01:16:25.295
(ALARM BLARING)

1450
01:16:26.262 --> 01:16:28.829
Oh, no! Come on. Hurry!

1451
01:16:32.996 --> 01:16:33.998
(COUGHING)

1452
01:16:34.663 --> 01:16:36.794
What now?

1453
01:16:36.796 --> 01:16:38.895
There's got to be another way out.

1454
01:16:38.897 --> 01:16:39.863
Dad, up there.

1455
01:16:41.563 --> 01:16:43.596
Let's check it out... Follow me.

1456
01:16:45.931 --> 01:16:47.130
(COUGHING)

1457
01:16:48.931 --> 01:16:53.129
Adam, watch where you step. Stay close.

1458
01:16:53.131 --> 01:16:55.497
Keep on going, I'm right behind you.

1459
01:17:03.198 --> 01:17:04.463
(COUGHING)

1460
01:17:04.465 --> 01:17:05.499
Up there.

1461
01:17:09.433 --> 01:17:10.666
(YELLS)

1462
01:17:14.934 --> 01:17:17.331
There's no way down. We're trapped.

1463
01:17:17.333 --> 01:17:18.500
No, Dad. Look.

1464
01:17:20.999 --> 01:17:22.000
- Zipline!
- Zipline!

1465
01:17:28.934 --> 01:17:30.198
Aah!

1466
01:17:30.200 --> 01:17:31.200
Oh, shoot.

1467
01:17:32.600 --> 01:17:33.568
(GRUNTING)

1468
01:17:35.835 --> 01:17:38.803
(LAUGHS) One way in, one way out.

1469
01:17:40.868 --> 01:17:41.869
We're going home.

1470
01:17:44.867 --> 01:17:47.703
Let me go, you big oaf. (PANTING)

1471
01:17:49.003 --> 01:17:51.201
So what'll it be?

1472
01:17:51.203 --> 01:17:55.033
Shall we end this little charade
and return you to your cell?

1473
01:17:55.035 --> 01:17:56.934
He's never going back there.

1474
01:17:56.936 --> 01:17:58.102
(GROANS)

1475
01:17:58.104 --> 01:17:59.071
Dad!

1476
01:18:01.837 --> 01:18:05.903
You silly beast. You lied to me.

1477
01:18:05.905 --> 01:18:10.336
You're not so special. The
boy has everything we need.

1478
01:18:10.338 --> 01:18:13.235
No, please. Leave him alone. You promised.

1479
01:18:13.237 --> 01:18:14.439
It's too late now.

1480
01:18:16.805 --> 01:18:18.338
(GROWLS)

1481
01:18:25.672 --> 01:18:29.436
I would've kept you
both, but I only need one.

1482
01:18:29.438 --> 01:18:30.707
No, please!

1483
01:18:31.772 --> 01:18:32.773
I'm sorry, son.

1484
01:18:35.606 --> 01:18:36.606
No!

1485
01:18:41.273 --> 01:18:42.805
No.

1486
01:18:42.807 --> 01:18:44.505
Argh! You animal!

1487
01:18:44.507 --> 01:18:47.442
(LAUGHS) Really, it's
you who is the animal.

1488
01:18:48.107 --> 01:18:50.406
(GRUNTING)

1489
01:18:50.408 --> 01:18:52.806
(CHUCKLES) I hate to break it to you,

1490
01:18:52.808 --> 01:18:54.972
but that's only a flare gun.

1491
01:18:54.974 --> 01:18:58.073
It won't do you any
good. Now get back inside,

1492
01:18:58.075 --> 01:18:59.473
we've got work to do.

1493
01:18:59.475 --> 01:19:02.108
No, you're out of business.

1494
01:19:19.642 --> 01:19:20.875
No!

1495
01:19:31.777 --> 01:19:32.745
(SCREAMING)

1496
01:19:47.446 --> 01:19:50.547
Don't just stand there, pull me up!

1497
01:19:55.612 --> 01:19:57.176
No!

1498
01:19:57.178 --> 01:19:58.344
(THUDS)

1499
01:19:58.346 --> 01:20:00.647
Ooh, that must hurt.

1500
01:20:05.980 --> 01:20:07.146
ADAM: Dad!

1501
01:20:07.947 --> 01:20:09.046
Dad!

1502
01:20:10.615 --> 01:20:11.615
Oh, oh...

1503
01:20:15.813 --> 01:20:18.782
Please, don't leave me.

1504
01:20:26.014 --> 01:20:29.349
BIGFOOT: <i>The healing touch, it
all goes with the territory.</i>

1505
01:20:34.782 --> 01:20:36.383
(BREATHING DEEPLY)

1506
01:20:38.583 --> 01:20:42.414
<i>♪♪ Do we know where
the light is the brightest?</i>

1507
01:20:42.416 --> 01:20:46.082
<i>♪♪ Do we know how to
clear what the fear is?</i>

1508
01:20:46.084 --> 01:20:49.482
<i>♪♪ Do we know how to
feel when we crave it?</i>

1509
01:20:49.484 --> 01:20:52.018
<i>♪♪ Do we know
what we are? ♪♪</i>

1510
01:20:54.750 --> 01:20:58.583
Look at that! He really is a bigfoot.

1511
01:20:58.585 --> 01:21:01.450
You see, you never listen
to me. I told you so!

1512
01:21:01.452 --> 01:21:03.249
Are you kidding?

1513
01:21:03.251 --> 01:21:05.952
<i>♪♪ Do we know
what we are? ♪♪</i>

1514
01:21:17.353 --> 01:21:18.687
(CRYING)

1515
01:21:25.287 --> 01:21:26.253
Adam?

1516
01:21:27.287 --> 01:21:28.254
Dad?

1517
01:21:30.020 --> 01:21:31.020
